2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20India%20Made%20Virtue%20Out%20of%20Necessity%20by%20Exporting%20Labour%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21173418%2FEffect-40.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20reported%20this%20week%20that%20India%20tops%20global%20charts%20with%20respect%20to%20inward%20Dollar%20remittances%20sent%20by%20non-resident%20Indians%20working%20overseas.%20At%20an%20estimated%20all-time%20high%20of%20%24125%20billion%2C%20remittances%20to%20India%20are%20more%20than%20double%20the%20%2450%20billion%20recorded%20by%20China.%20Taking%20some%20credit%20for%20such%20remittances%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20earlier%20this%20year%20assured%20H-1B%20visa%20holders%20in%20the%20United%20States%20that%20he%20would%20help%20shape%20policies%20and%20agreements%20that%20would%20shape%20the%20%E2%80%9Clives%2C%20dreams%20and%20destinies%E2%80%9D%20of%20Indians%20awaiting%20the%20renewal%20of%20such%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuccessive%20governments%20have%20long%20been%20in%20the%20business%20of%20demanding%20overseas%20employment%20opportunities%20for%20Indians%2C%20equating%20it%20to%20demands%20for%20normal%20market%20access%20under%20multilateral%20rules%20for%20trade.%20Here%2C%20however%2C%20is%20the%20downside.%20While%20Indians%20working%20overseas%20and%20contributing%20to%20the%20economic%20growth%20of%20other%20economies%2C%20mostly%20more%20developed%20than%20India%2C%20send%20home%20increasing%20amounts%20of%20money%2C%20China%20continues%20to%20earn%20vast%20sums%20of%20foreign%20exchange%20exporting%20manufactures.%20India%E2%80%99s%20merchandise%20exports%20have%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20shrunk%20during%202023%20from%20US%20%24452%20billion%20to%20%24429%20billion.%20A%20decline%20of%20around%205%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20the%20Indian%20economy%20is%20still%20unable%20to%20make%20a%20mark%20in%20the%20export%20of%20goods%2C%20while%20it%20increasingly%20benefits%20from%20the%20export%20of%20human%20capital.%20Homeward%20remittances%20sent%20by%20Indians%20working%20overseas%20continue%20to%20help%20the%20country%20manage%20its%20balance%20of%20payments%20and%20keep%20the%20deficit%20on%20the%20external%20account%20in%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERise%20of%20%E2%80%98remittance%E2%80%99%20economy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%20Kerala%20in%20the%201970s%20that%20economists%20first%20took%20note%20of%20the%20economic%20benefits%20of%20human%20capital%20export.%20As%20demand%20for%20skilled%20labour%20began%20to%20rise%20in%20the%20post-oil%20boom%20economies%20of%20the%20Gulf%2C%20skilled%20labour%20from%20Kerala%20was%20quick%20to%20grasp%20the%20opportunity.%20As%20a%20state%20that%20had%20invested%20in%20education%20and%20skill%20development%20but%20had%20not%20been%20able%20to%20create%20local%20employment%20opportunities%20in%20the%20industrial%20economy%2C%20Kerala%20was%20saddled%20with%20skilled%20but%20unemployed%20youth.%20The%20state%20had%20a%20historical%20and%20geographical%20connection%20to%20the%20Gulf%20that%20it%20exploited%20successfully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Dollars%20kept%20coming%20in%2C%20Kerala%20was%20also%20berated%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98remittance%E2%80%99%20economy%20%E2%80%93%20a%20feature%20of%20other%20industrially%20less%20developed%20economies%20like%20Nepal%20and%20the%20Philippines.%20Unable%20to%20export%20value-added%20manufactures%2C%20such%20%E2%80%98remittance%E2%80%99%20economies%20export%20labour.%20Within%20India%2C%20less%20developed%20states%20like%20Bihar%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20have%20become%20remittance-based%20economies%20with%20migrant%20labour%20from%20the%20more%20developed%20peninsular%20states%20sending%20money%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21170713%2FEffect-39.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221050%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21170713%2FEffect-39.jpg%201050w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21170713%2FEffect-39-300x140.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21170713%2FEffect-39-1024x477.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690211%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22489%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentaional%20image.%20Photo%3A%20flickr.com%2FWen-Yan%20King%2FCC%20BY-NC-SA%202.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20merchandise%20exports%2C%20especially%20of%20manufactured%20goods%2C%20not%20picking%20up%20and%20services%20exports%2C%20especially%20of%20skilled%20labour%20services%2C%20doing%20well%2C%20India%20made%20a%20virtue%20of%20a%20necessity.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%201990s%2C%20securing%20a%20multilateral%20regime%20for%20labour%20services%20exports%20became%20a%20mantra%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20trade%20policy.%20Both%20in%20multilateral%20trade%20negotiations%2C%20under%20the%20auspices%20of%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%2C%20and%20in%20bilateral%20trade%20agreements%2C%20India%20kept%20demanding%20rules-based%20access%20for%20services%20exports%2C%20including%20labour%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20the%20year%202000%20and%20the%20Y2K%20opportunity%20that%20showed%20the%20world%20that%20India%20could%20also%20export%20technically%20skilled%20manpower%20and%20not%20just%20construction%20labour.%20So%20the%20economic%20base%20of%20the%20services%20export%20economy%20moved%20beyond%20Kerala%20to%20include%20neighbouring%20states%20that%20had%20invested%20in%20engineering%20and%20computer%20software%20training.%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20Telangana%20became%20important%20sources%20of%20software%20services%20personnel.%20The%20H1B%20visa%20route%20to%20the%20United%20States%20became%20a%20passport%20to%20prosperity%20for%20thousands%20of%20young%20men%20and%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20share%20of%20trade%20in%20services%20boomed%2C%20increasing%20from%20an%20average%20of%203%25%20of%20national%20income%20(gross%20domestic%20product)%20in%20the%201990s%20to%20an%20average%20of%20over%2010%25%20by%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20and%20the%20share%20of%20inward%20personal%20remittances%20of%20overseas%20Indians%20increased%20from%20an%20average%20of%201%25%20of%20GDP%20in%20the%201990s%20to%20over%203%25%20of%20GDP%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20In%20absolute%20terms%2C%20remittances%20have%20increased%20from%20an%20average%20of%20around%20%245%20billion%20in%20the%201990s%20to%20over%20%2465%20billion%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20This%20number%20has%20just%20hit%20%24125%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20even%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20merchandise%20exports%20remain%20stagnant%2C%20even%20declining%20at%20times%2C%20her%20ability%20to%20earn%20Dollars%20from%20the%20export%20of%20skilled%20and%20highly%20skilled%20labour%20remains%20robust.%20While%20economists%20have%20for%20long%20associated%20such%20a%20structure%20of%20a%20remittance-based%20economy%20with%20economic%20backwardness%2C%20successive%20governments%20have%20interpreted%20this%20as%20evidence%20of%20growing%20global%20demand%20for%20Indian%20talent.%20Not%20to%20be%20left%20behind%20the%20media%20too%20keeps%20its%20focus%20on%20what%20the%20government%20is%20able%20to%20do%20to%20secure%20more%20visas%20for%20Indians%20seeking%20employment%20overseas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20system%20germinated%20under%20colonial%20rule%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20century%20ago%2C%20India%20became%20an%20important%20source%20of%20what%20was%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%98indentured%20labour%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20virtual%20slaves%20shipped%20out%20from%20Bihar%2C%20Bengal%20and%20villages%20along%20the%20Coromandel%20Coast%20to%20distant%20islands%20from%20Fiji%20in%20the%20Pacific%20to%20Surinam%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20to%20work%20on%20sugar%20and%20rubber%20plantations.%20A%20century%20later%20Indian%20labour%20travels%20voluntarily%20overseas%20in%20search%20of%20employment%20and%20income%2C%20with%20the%20government%20helping%20secure%20visas.%20If%20the%20British%20imperial%20government%20facilitated%20the%20export%20of%20labour%20then%2C%20now%20the%20government%20of%20democratic%20India%20seeks%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20albeit%20under%20different%20contractual%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20for%20many%20years%2C%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20of%20Indian%20sweated%20labour%20in%20the%20Gulf%20was%20not%20very%20different%20from%20that%20of%20the%20indentured%20labour%20of%20colonial%20times.%20The%20poverty-stricken%20labour%20of%20British%20India%20that%20was%20shipped%20off%20to%20plantation%20islands%20of%20the%20Pacific%20and%20the%20Atlantic%20also%20went%20there%20on%20the%20assurance%20of%20a%20better%20life%20and%20income%20that%20could%20be%20taken%20back%20home.%20It%20was%20in%20search%20of%20such%20%E2%80%98remittances%E2%80%99%20that%20they%20too%20went%20to%20be%20virtually%20enslaved.%20The%20human%20indignities%20that%20many%20Gulf%20labour%20faced%20till%20the%20government%20of%20India%20stepped%20in%20and%20demanded%20better%20living%20conditions%20for%20them%20were%20no%20different%20from%20those%20faced%20by%20indentured%20labour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahatma%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20opposed%20the%20indentured%20labour%20system%20and%20ensured%20that%20it%20was%20brought%20to%20an%20end%20and%20the%20conditions%20of%20living%20of%20overseas%20Indians%20improved.%20A%20century%20later%20democratic%20India%20too%20intervenes%20similarly%20but%20continues%20to%20value%20the%20remittances%20that%20accrue%20to%20the%20Indian%20economy%20in%20return%20for%20the%20export%20of%20labour%2C%20sweated%20and%20skilled.%20Many%20who%20had%20gone%20in%20search%20of%20income%20have%20since%20opted%20to%20settle%20down%20in%20their%20host%20countries.%20This%20too%20is%20not%20very%20different%20from%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20children%20of%20indentured%20labour%20across%20the%20Commonwealth%20who%20opted%20to%20continue%20to%20live%20in%20the%20host%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20informed%20parliament%20that%20a%20total%20of%2016%2C63%2C440%20Indian%20citizens%20had%20%E2%80%9Crenounced%20their%20Indian%20citizenship%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20period%202011-22%2C%20and%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20number%20of%20Indian%20nationals%20exploring%20the%20global%20workplace%20has%20been%20significant%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades.%20Many%20of%20them%20have%20chosen%20to%20take%20up%20foreign%20citizenship%20for%20reasons%20of%20personal%20convenience.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorians%20and%20novelists%20have%20written%20eloquently%20and%20poignantly%20about%20the%20inhuman%20and%20exploitative%20nature%20of%20the%20colonial%20indentured%20labour%20system%20of%20the%20late%2019th%20to%20early%2020th%20Century.%20Ironically%2C%20though%2C%20today%E2%80%99s%20politicians%2C%20officials%20and%20economists%20celebrate%20labour%20export%20and%20the%20foreign%20exchange%20earned%20as%20a%20benefit%20of%20globalisation.%20Unable%20to%20provide%20adequate%20gainful%20employment%20opportunities%20at%20home%20India%20continues%20to%20justify%20seeking%20overseas%20employment%20opportunities%20for%20its%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703163632000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21173418%2FEffect-40.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fhow-india-made-virtue-out-of-necessity-by-exporting-labour%22%2C