autonomously%20created%20a%20light%20beacon%20and%20other%20items.%3Cp%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20UK's%20supreme%20court%20has%20ruled%20that%20AI%20cannot%20be%20named%20as%20an%20inventor.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20computer%20scientist%20lost%20an%20attempt%20to%20register%20patents%20for%20inventions%20he%20said%20were%20made%20by%20an%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Intellectual%20Property%20Office%2C%20High%20Court%2C%20and%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20previously%20made%20the%20same%20ruling.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supremecourt.uk%2Fcases%2Fuksc-2021-0201.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20UK's%20supreme%20court%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehas%20ruled%20that%20AI%20cannot%20be%20named%20as%20an%20inventor%20and%20secure%20patent%20rights.%20It%20follows%20earlier%20decisions%20from%20lower%20courts%20that%20reached%20the%20same%20conclusions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20US%20computer%20scientist%20Stephen%20Thaler%20lost%20his%20attempt%20to%20register%20patents%20for%20inventions%20he%20says%20were%20created%20by%20his%20AI%20system%2C%20DABUS.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThaler%20said%20DABUS%20autonomously%20created%20a%20light%20beacon%20and%20a%20container%20for%20food%20and%20drink%2C%20and%20entitled%20to%20rights%20over%20the%20inventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK's%20Intellectual%20Property%20Office%20had%20previously%20denied%20the%20request%2C%20concluding%20that%20an%20inventor%20must%20be%20a%20human%20if%20it%20wanted%20to%20apply%20for%20patents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThaler's%20lawyers%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fai-cannot-be-patent-inventor-uk-supreme-court-rules-landmark-case-2023-12-20%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshared%20with%20Reuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20ruling%20%26quot%3Bestablishes%20that%20UK%20patent%20law%20is%20currently%20wholly%20unsuitable%20for%20protecting%20inventions%20gener