rahat%20daal%20diye%2C%20lekin%20badla%20kya%20hai%3F%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%5BYou%20have%20removed%20the%20horns%20from%20the%20demon%E2%80%99s%20head%20and%20put%20a%20smile%20on%20his%20face.%20But%20has%20anything%20really%20changed%3F%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESo%20what%20did%20he%20say%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20said%20absolutely%20nothing%20for%20the%20first%2010%20minutes.%20There%20was%20a%20commercial%20break%2C%20he%20walked%20out%20of%20the%20room.%20Maybe%20he%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20pee%20or%20something%2C%20and%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20return.%20When%20he%20had%20returned%20after%20four%20or%20five%20minutes%2C%20I%20walked%20up%20to%20the%20next%20door%20room%20and%20I%20said%20what%E2%80%99s%20happened%2C%20you%20haven%E2%80%99t%20come%20back.%20And%20he%20said%20but%20if%20you%20think%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20%3Cem%3Erakshas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20point%20of%20talking%20to%20me.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Advani%2C%20that%20was%20just%20a%20turn%20of%20phrase%20and%20nothing%20more.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20to%20be%20offensive.%20I%20was%20simply%20saying%20that%20you%20are%20deliberately%20changing%20the%20%3Cem%3Erakshas%3C%2Fem%3E%20image%20of%20the%20BJP%20into%20a%20softer%20gentler%20image%20to%20make%20yourself%20politically%20more%20electable.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20understood%20and%20he%20walked%20back%20in.%20When%20he%20sat%20down%20he%20did%20something%20for%20which%20I%20would%20never%20cease%20to%20praise%20him.%20He%20got%20up%20from%20his%20chair%20after%20he%20sat%20down%20and%20he%20went%20to%20every%20single%20member%20of%20the%20crew%20and%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20terribly%20sorry%2C%20I%20made%20a%20horrible%20mistake%2C%20forgive%20me.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHorrible%20mistake%20for%20what%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20having%20walked%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAh!%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20sat%20down%20and%20he%20continued%20the%20interview%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99ll%20give%20you%20one%20more%20example.%20This%20particular%20example%20is%20from%20February%201998.%20%5BThe%20second%20example%20is%20from%5D%20my%20very%20first%20interview%20with%20him%2C%20%5Bit%5D%20would%20have%20been%20in%201990%2C%20it%20was%20for%20the%20pilot%20episode%20of%20%E2%80%98Eyewitness%E2%80%99%20%5Ba%20show%20that%20Thapar%20hosted%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20was%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition.%20He%20had%20just%20finished%20that%20famous%20yatra.%20I%20interviewed%20him%20for%2010%20minutes.%20He%20was%20fine%2C%20he%20was%20happy.%20He%20gave%20me%20a%20cup%20of%20tea%2C%20and%20I%20wandered%20off.%20Three%20or%20four%20months%20later%2C%20%E2%80%98Eyewitness%E2%80%99%20came%20out%20and%20I%20met%20him%20outside%20Vajpayee%E2%80%99s%20house.%20Vajpayee%20lived%20in%20Raisina%20Road%20in%20those%20days.%20I%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9COh%20hello%2C%20Mr%20Advani%2C%20how%20are%20you%3F%20Did%20you%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20see%20the%20interview%3F%E2%80%9D%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%2C%20I%20haven%E2%80%99t%20seen%20the%20interview%2C%20but%20I%20gather%20it%20was%20a%20travesty%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20very%20happy.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20was%20the%20problem%20with%20it%3F%E2%80%9D%20I%20said%20it%E2%80%99s%20exactly%20as%20recorded%20and%20you%20were%20quite%20happy%2C%20you%20gave%20me%20a%20cup%20of%20tea%20afterwards.%20Anyway%2C%20he%20walked%20in%2C%20ignored%20me.%20I%20sent%20him%20a%20video%20of%20the%20interview%20and%20I%20said%20please%20have%20a%20look%20at%20it%2C%20this%20is%20exactly%20as%20recorded.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20months%20went%20by%2C%20not%20a%20word%20from%20him%2C%20and%20I%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9COh%2C%20to%20hel