0involving%20sexual%20abuse%20of%20a%2017-year-old%20student.%20Records%20show%20they%20responded%20promptly%2C%20putting%20the%20teacher%2C%20Sterrett%20Oney%20Neale%2C%20on%20paid%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20than%20a%20year%20before%20the%20arrest%2C%20in%20August%202017%2C%20an%20administrator%20at%20the%20school%2C%20West%20High%2C%20had%20reported%20seeing%20Neale%20alone%20with%20the%20student%20in%20his%20classroom%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20school%20year%2C%20according%20to%20subsequent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233962-victim-testimony-during-salt-lake-city-criminal-case-against-sterrett-oney-neale%23document%2Fp68%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecourt%20testimony%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20administrators%20told%20Neale%20to%20stop%20spending%20time%20alone%20with%20her%2C%20the%20teenager%20said%20in%20court%2C%20she%20defended%20him%20%E2%80%94%20something%20a%20trained%20investigator%20would%20know%20is%20common%20in%20cases%20of%20grooming.%20In%20the%20records%20released%20to%20me%20by%20the%20district%2C%20there's%20no%20documentation%20of%20a%20formal%20investigation%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20student's%20testimony%2C%20offered%20during%20a%20preliminary%20hearing%20in%20Neale's%20ongoing%20criminal%20trial%2C%20made%20clear%20that%20the%20classroom%20encounter%20was%20a%20red%20flag.%20She%20described%20how%20Neale%20had%20been%20a%20source%20of%20support%20as%20she%20was%20grieving%20the%20death%20of%20her%20grandmother%20and%20how%20he'd%20helped%20her%20report%20abuse%20she'd%20experienced%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20another%20teacher%20during%20summer%20camp.%20How%20Neale%20directed%20her%20in%20school%20plays%20and%20even%20advised%20her%20on%20a%20research%20paper%20about%20the%20psychological%20effects%20of%20child%20sexual%20abuse.%20And%20how%20he%20then%20kissed%20and%20touched%20her%20in%20that%20same%20classroom%2C%20which%20led%20to%20months%20of%20sexual%20encounters%20at%20his%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20student's%20testimony%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Sterrett%20Oney%20Neale%2C%20who%20she%20says%20had%20sex%20with%20her%20repeatedly%20when%20she%20was%20a%20minor.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581d29ecefc010bea24fe78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22537%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20former%20Salt%20Lake%20City%20student%20testifies%20about%20the%20day%20an%20administrator%20saw%20her%20alone%20in%20a%20classroom%20with%20her%20teacher%2C%20Sterrett%20Oney%20Neale.%20It%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20missed%20opportunity%20to%20halt%20months%20of%20sexual%20abuse.%3Cp%3ESalt%20Lake%20City%20District%20Court%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20allowed%20Neale%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24234030-salt-lake-city-voluntary-resignation-agreement-teacher-sterrett-oney-neale%23document%2Fp3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evoluntarily%20resign%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20school%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20paid%20his%20salary%20through%20the%20end%20of%20his%20contract%20that%20August.%20(Neale's%20attorney%20declined%20to%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20across%20another%20disturbing%20case%20from%20several%20years%20ago%20in%20Durham%20County%2C%20North%20Carolina.%20There%2C%20a%20student%20at%20Neal%20Middle%20School%20said%20her%20chorus%20teacher%2C%20Troy%20Logan%20Pickens%2C%20had%20groped%20her.%20(She%20only%20disclosed%20later%2C%20in%20high%20school%2C%20that%20he'd%20raped%20her.)%20An%20interim%20principal%2C%20James%20Key%2C%20didn't%20open%20an%20investigation%20until%20the%20child's%20mother%20got%20involved%2C%20and%20even%20then%2C%20according%20to%20a%20subsequent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233964-civil-suit-against-wake-county-and-durham-county-schools-in-case-of-troy-logan-pickens%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecivil%20suit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20settled%20out%20of%20court%2C%20failed%20to%20report%20the%20groping%20allegation%20to%20law%20enforcement%20or%20child%20protective%20services%2C%20as%20required%20by%20state%20law.%20Instead%2C%20Key%20allowed%20Pickens%20to%20resign%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20him%20to%20continue%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neal%20Middle%20School%20in%20Durham%2C%20North%20Carolina%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580933350edbc52a8655777%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221665%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENeal%20Middle%20School%20in%20Durham%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20where%20a%20student%20reported%20that%20her%20teacher%2C%20Troy%20Logan%20Pickens%2C%20had%20groped%20her.%20He%20was%20later%20convicted%20of%20rape.%3Cp%3EAndrea%20Bruce%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMonths%20later%2C%20Pickens%20applied%20for%20another%20teaching%20job%2C%20in%20nearby%20Wake%20County.%20He%20landed%20the%20job%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20a%20positive%20review%20from%20Key%2C%20who%2C%20according%20to%20the%20civil%20suit%2C%20shared%20nothing%20about%20his%20misconduct%20investigation.%20(Key%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20long%2C%20Pickens%20sexually%20abused%20a%20student%20at%20the%20new%20school.%20The%20methodical%20assaults%20in%20a%20school%20bathroom%2C%20detailed%20in%20court%20records%2C%20included%20digital%20penetration%20and%20forced%20fellatio.%20The%20student%20only%20came%20forward%20about%20the%20abuse%20two%20years%20later%2C%20after%20Pickens%20was%20arrested%20for%20raping%20the%20student%20back%20at%20Neal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20in%20Durham%20County%2C%20the%20Wake%20County%20district%20allowed%20Pickens%20to%20resign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHundreds%20of%20Rosemeads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20I%20explored%20how%20the%20culture%20of%20a%20single%20Southern%20California%20high%20school%20%E2%80%94%20my%20alma%20mater%2C%20Rosemead%20High%20%E2%80%94%20became%20a%20stalking%20ground%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2F40-years-of-sexual-misconduct-at-rosemead-california-high-school-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echild%20predators%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20spent%20years%20trying%20to%20get%20to%20the%20heart%20of%20what%20went%20wrong%20there%2C%20first%20with%20an%20investigation%20into%20my%20former%20journalism%20teacher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frosemead-high-eric-burgess-sexual-misconduct-investigation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEric%20Burgess%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20then%2C%20after%20receiving%20a%20flood%20of%20tips%20about%20other%20Rosemead%20teachers%2C%20by%20detailing%2040%20years%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2F40-years-of-sexual-misconduct-at-rosemead-california-high-school-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esexual%20abuse%20and%20misconduct%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20more%20I%20uncovered%2C%20the%20more%20I%20began%20to%20wonder%20whether%20Rosemead%20was%20unique.%20Or%20whether%20a%20broader%20lens%20would%20reveal%20similar%20patterns%20of%20behavior%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20federal%20agency%20tracks%20teacher%20sexual%20misconduct.%20So%20I%20requested%20disciplinary%20records%20and%20severance%20agreements%20from%20the%2010%20largest%20school%20districts%20in%20all%2050%20states%2C%20as%20well%20as%20license%20revocations%20from%20every%20state's%20department%20of%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpposition%20to%20disclosing%20these%20records%20was%20fierce.%20In%20several%20states%2C%20including%20Alabama%2C%20Iowa%2C%20and%20Virginia%2C%20their%20largest%20districts%20refused%20to%20release%20any%20records.%20Many%20districts%20demanded%20prohibitive%20sums%20of%20money%20to%20fulfill%20requests.%20The%20Hawaii%20Department%20of%20Education%20asked%20for%20%2475%2C060.%20The%20Katy%20Independent%20School%20District%20in%20Texas%20wanted%20%24125%2C352.%20Lincoln%20Public%20Schools%20in%20Nebraska%20invoiced%20%24243%2C836.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20districts%20never%20provided%20records%2C%20even%20places%20such%20as%20Alaska's%20Bering%20Strait%20School%20District%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nomenugget.com%2Fnews%2Fbssd-pay-126-million-student-sex-abuse-case%23%3A~%3Atext%3DYoung%2520victims%2520and%2520their%2520parents%2Cnorthwest%2520Alaska%2520village%2520of%2520Wales.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Fschool-district-that-employed-principal-despite-sex-abuse-complaints-will-pay-3-8-million-to-his-victims%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteachers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20criminally%20convicted%20in%20recent%20years%20for%20abusing%20students.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20is%20digital%2C%20so%20it%20is%20tedious%20research%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20district%20official%20told%20me.%20Some%2C%20such%20as%20Springfield%20Public%20Schools%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20argued%20that%20releasing%20records%20would%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Binvasion%20of%20the%20teachers'%20privacy%20outweighing%20any%20possible%20right%20of%20the%20public%20to%20know.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ben%20Franklin%20Career%20Center%20in%20Dunbar%2C%20West%20Virginia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581c8d91c5c7b8c9a09b862%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20district%20official%20said%20Ben%20Franklin%20Career%20Center%20in%20Dunbar%2C%20West%20Virginia%2C%20was%20never%20asked%20for%20the%20personnel%20file%20of%20Kevin%20Dean%20Neal%2C%20a%20teacher%20who%20was%20later%20convicted%20of%20sexually%20abusing%20a%20student%20at%20his%20next%20school.%3Cp%3EMaddie%20McGarvey%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20we%20received%20more%20than%20800%20disciplinary%20files%20from%2085%20school%20districts%20in%2034%20states.%20Many%20of%20the%20records%20were%20partially%20redacted%20or%20incomplete%2C%20but%20388%20files%20included%20enough%20detail%20to%20determine%20they%20were%20related%20to%20sexual%20misconduct%20with%20students.%20We%20also%20obtained%20more%20than%203%2C700%20teacher%20severance%20agreements.%20We%20supplemented%20these%20documents%20with%20teacher%20union%20contracts%2C%20court%20and%20law-enforcement%20records%2C%20a%20database%20of%20news%20coverage%20of%20educator%20arrests%2C%20and%20a%20review%20of%20employee%20policies%20from%20the%20largest%20school%20districts%20in%20every%20state%20to%20see%20what%20behavior%20they%20do%20%E2%80%94%20and%20don't%20%E2%80%94%20prohibit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaken%20together%2C%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20pages%20of%20records%2C%20combined%20with%20interviews%20with%20school%20administrators%2C%20state%20investigators%2C%20liability-insurance%20reps%2C%20lawyers%2C%20and%20academic%20experts%2C%20indicate%20that%20there%20may%20be%20hundreds%20of%20Rosemead%20Highs%20across%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20and%20provide%20a%20window%20into%20how%20abuse%20has%20been%20allowed%20to%20fester.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20national%20panic%20about%20child%20%26quot%3Bgroomers%26quot%3B%20has%20dominated%20public%20discourse%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20sparking%20hundreds%20of%20school%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Feducation%2F2023%2F07%2F12%2Fgrooming-racist-why-adults-are-waging-war-childrens-picture-books-or-inside-adult-war-childrens-picture-books%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebook%20bans%3C%2Fa%3E%20targeting%20LGBTQ%20content%20and%20a%20dozen%20state%20bills%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6260421%2Ftennessee-limiting-drag-shows-status-of-anti-drag-bills-u-s%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecriminalizing%20drag%20performances%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20children.%20But%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenoughabuse.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F2023-Call-to-Action-Report-September-Update.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20state%20legislatures%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20taken%20steps%20during%20the%20same%20two%20years%20to%20block%20documented%20predators%20from%20continued%20access%20to%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20more%20about%20high%20school%20sexual%20misconduct%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frosemead-high-eric-burgess-sexual-misconduct-investigation%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22d979133fa1b7f13ccbab973f697abcc9%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frosemead-high-eric-burgess-sexual-misconduct-investigation%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EHe%20was%20my%20high%20school%20journalism%20teacher.%20Then%20I%20investigated%20his%20relationships%20with%20teenage%20girls.%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feric-burgess-rosemead-high-sexual-misconduct-district-failures-2022-5%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22a4c12571c6023ae94923286cbad63210%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feric-burgess-rosemead-high-sexual-misconduct-district-failures-2022-5%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EHow%20a%20Southern%20California%20high%20school%20shielded%20a%20beloved%20teacher%20who%20groomed%20students%20for%20sex%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frosemead-high-in-turmoil-after-eric-burgess-exposed-for-sexual-abuse-2022-6%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22c87a2ffaa491041b1140b14bed0086ca%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frosemead-high-in-turmoil-after-eric-burgess-exposed-for-sexual-abuse-2022-6%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EPain%2C%20anger%2C%20and%20disgust%3A%20Inside%20Rosemead%20High's%20reckoning%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scope%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20larger%20than%20previously%20known.%20At%20least%201%2C895%20teachers%20have%20had%20adverse%20action%20taken%20against%20their%20credential%20by%20state%20education%20licensing%20boards%20from%202017%20to%202022%20for%20sexual%20misconduct%2C%20according%20to%20data%20collected%20by%20the%20nonprofit%20National%20Association%20of%20State%20Directors%20of%20Teacher%20Education%20and%20Certification%2C%20or%20NASDTEC.%20The%20figure%2C%20provided%20exclusively%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20is%20almost%20certainly%20an%20undercount%2C%20as%20many%20states%20do%20not%20report%20details%20of%20why%20a%20credential%20was%20suspended%20or%20revoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20analyzed%20a%20database%20of%20local%20news%20stories%20collected%20by%20Billie-Jo%20Grant%2C%20a%20leading%20researcher%20on%20sexual%20abuse%20in%20schools%2C%20and%20her%20students%20at%20Cal%20Poly%20San%20Luis%20Obispo%20and%20found%20that%20at%20least%203%2C045%20school%20staffers%20have%20been%20arrested%20since%202017%20following%20allegations%20of%20sexual%20misconduct%20involving%20students.%20This%20includes%20both%20licensed%20teachers%20and%20noncredentialed%20staff%2C%20from%20janitors%20to%20teachers'%20aides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20frequency%20of%20the%20abuse%2C%20we%20found%20a%20fragmented%20approach%20to%20accountability%20that%20leaves%20oversight%20largely%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20administrators%20at%20each%20of%20the%2013%2C000%20school%20districts%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20They%20are%20in%20turn%20governed%20by%20a%20patchwork%20system%20of%20state%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20documents%20we%20obtained%20lay%20bare%20the%20life%20cycle%20of%20sexual%20abuse%20in%20schools%2C%20documenting%20how%20administrators%20and%20policymakers%20have%20failed%20students%20at%20every%20turn%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EA%20third%20of%20districts%20we%20examined%20have%20threadbare%20policies%20that%20bar%20sexual%20misconduct%20but%20do%20not%20prohibit%20widely%20recognized%20sexual%20grooming%20behaviors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDistrict%20officials%20often%20conduct%20cursory%20investigations%2C%20sometimes%20interviewing%20only%20the%20accused%20educator%20before%20finding%20claims%20unsubstantiated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EDistricts%20routinely%20mete%20out%20mild%20sanctions%20such%20as%20reprimands%20or%20suspensions%2C%20and%20they%20often%20allow%20teachers%20who%20engaged%20in%20abuse%20to%20resign%20or%20retire.%20Only%2015%25%20of%20the%20cases%20we%20analyzed%20resulted%20in%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ELegislators%20have%20failed%20to%20keep%20abusers%20from%20moving%20on%20to%20other%20schools%3B%20only%2017%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20require%20districts%20to%20disclose%20information%20to%20prospective%20employers%20about%20an%20allegation%2C%20investigation%2C%20resignation%2C%20or%20termination%20related%20to%20teacher%20sexual%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EA%20culture%20of%20silence%20dominates%2C%20with%20widespread%20use%20of%20nondisclosure%20clauses%20in%20severance%20agreements%20and%20strict%20union%20confidentiality%20language%20protecting%20teacher%20personnel%20files.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20national%20database%20that%20tracks%20teachers%20who've%20lost%20their%20license%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20sexual%20misconduct%20is%20voluntary%20and%20nonpublic%3B%20state%20credentialing%20agencies%20all%20participate%2C%20but%20just%202%25%20of%20school%20districts%20opt%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bottom%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20Grant%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20that%20we've%20collectively%20valued%20the%20reputations%20of%20teachers%20over%20the%20safety%20of%20students.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftbimedia.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbistudios%2F_00%2Fdev_edit%2Fgraphics%2F2023%2F12%2F2023-12-rosemead-national-1%2Findex.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-chart%3D%5C%22scrolly%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20failure%20to%20prevent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20school%20district%20we%20examined%20has%20some%20kind%20of%20sexual-misconduct%20policy%20in%20place%3B%20a%20typical%20one%20from%20Lee%20County%2C%20Florida%2C%20prohibits%20employees%20from%20%26quot%3Bengaging%20in%20or%20soliciting%20sexual%2C%20romantic%2C%20or%20lewd%20conduct%20with%20a%20student.%26quot%3B%20But%20of%20the%20more%20than%20150%20policies%20from%20large%20districts%20we%20reviewed%2C%20a%20third%20fail%20to%20prohibit%20grooming%20or%20boundary-violating%20behaviors%20that%20can%20lay%20the%20groundwork%20for%20sexual%20abuse.%20The%20most%20thorough%20policies%20are%20explicit%20in%20naming%20unacceptable%20behaviors%2C%20such%20as%20giving%20students%20gifts%2C%20texting%20them%2C%20or%20spending%20time%20alone%20with%20a%20student%20in%20an%20isolated%20classroom%20%E2%80%94%20as%20Sterrett%20Neale%20did%20in%20Salt%20Lake%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20policy%20manual%20for%20Putnam%20County%20Schools%20in%20West%20Virginia%20lacks%20these%20prohibitions.%20The%20manual%20clearly%20defines%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20bans%20%26quot%3Bamorous%20relationships%26quot%3B%20between%20employees%20and%20students.%20But%20it%20doesn't%20provide%20guidelines%20for%20teachers%20on%20maintaining%20appropriate%20boundaries%2C%20which%20experts%20say%20is%20often%20where%20abuse%20begins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22973%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Top%3A%20An%20example%20of%20a%20detailed%20employee%20policy%20that%20clearly%20defines%20teacher-student%20boundaries%3B%20Bottom%3A%20An%20example%20of%20a%20cursory%20employee%20policy%20doesn't%20define%20appropriate%20boundaries%20or%20grooming%20behaviors.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658332facefc010bea25b0b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22971%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20district%20employee%20policies%20clearly%20define%20boundary%20violations%20and%20bar%20specific%20grooming%20behaviors%2C%20as%20in%20this%20Salt%20Lake%20City%20Schools%20policy%2C%20top.%20But%20many%20do%20little%20more%20than%20prohibit%20student-teacher%20sexual%20relationships%2C%20as%20in%20this%20Putnam%20County%20Schools%20policy%2C%20bottom.%3Cp%3ETop%3A%20Salt%20Lake%20City%20Schools%3B%20Bottom%3A%20Putnam%20County%20Schools%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAgainst%20the%20backdrop%20of%20these%20weak%20guidelines%2C%20Kevin%20Dean%20Neal%2C%20a%20law%20and%20public%20safety%20teacher%20at%20the%20Putnam%20Career%20and%20Technical%20Center%20vocational%20school%2C%20cultivated%20a%20sexual%20relationship%20with%20a%20student.%20After%20her%20classmates%20reported%20their%20suspicions%20to%20a%20counselor%20in%20late%202017%2C%20an%20assistant%20principal%20picked%20up%20the%20student%20from%20class%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233972-putnam-county-schools-notes-file-for-sexual-abuse-by-teacher-kevin-dean-neal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigative%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%2C%20and%20she%20confirmed%20that%20Neal%20had%20sex%20with%20her.%20It%20started%2C%20a%20classmate%20said%2C%20when%20Neal%20began%20giving%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20treatment%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20girl%20and%20spending%20time%20with%20her%20between%20classes%2C%20including%20alone%20in%20his%20office.%20The%20singling%20out%20and%20the%20one-on-one%20time%20are%20both%20recognizable%20behaviors%20that%20an%20anti-grooming%20policy%20could%20have%20prohibited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeal%20was%20suspended.%20Then%2C%20like%20many%20teachers%20before%20and%20since%2C%20he%20asked%20the%20student%20he'd%20groomed%20to%20participate%20in%20a%20cover-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20deny%20it%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Neal%20told%20the%20girl%20in%20a%20string%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233972-putnam-county-schools-notes-file-for-sexual-abuse-by-teacher-kevin-dean-neal%23document%2Fp6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edigital%20communications%3C%2Fa%3E%20uncovered%20by%20investigators.%20%26quot%3BThey%20will%20probably%20want%20to%20download%20our%20phones%20so%20make%20sure%20your%20txt%2C%20emails%2C%20social%20media%20is%20all%20clean%20from%20anything%20that%20has%20to%20do%20with%20us.%26quot%3B%20(Neither%20Neal%20nor%20his%20attorney%20responded%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22636%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emails%20showing%20West%20Virginia%20vocational%20school%20teacher%20Kevin%20Neal%20telling%20a%20student%20to%20delete%20all%20digital%20communications%20evidencing%20their%20sexual%20relationship.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581da8fa79e5746976b096b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20a%20student%20was%20asked%20by%20administrators%20at%20West%20Virginia's%20Putnam%20Career%20and%20Technical%20Center%20whether%20she%20was%20in%20a%20sexual%20relationship%20with%20her%20teacher%20Kevin%20Neal%2C%20he%20tried%20to%20enlist%20her%20in%20a%20cover-up.%3Cp%3EPutnam%20County%20Schools%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20strong%20policies%20do%20exist%20on%20paper%2C%20attorneys%2C%20school%20insurance%20representatives%2C%20and%20state%20department-of-education%20investigators%20I%20spoke%20with%20described%20training%20as%20bare%20bones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMary%20Jo%20McGrath%2C%20a%20lawyer%20in%20Santa%20Barbara%2C%20California%2C%20spent%20decades%20bringing%20child-abuse%20cases%20and%20developed%20a%20training%20program%20to%20assist%20school%20administrators%20in%20rooting%20out%20abuse.%20But%20while%20many%20California%20districts%20have%20adopted%20aspects%20of%20her%20curriculum%2C%20she%20said%20most%20districts%20%26quot%3Bdo%20the%20bare%20minimum%26quot%3B%20in%20educating%20staff%20to%20identify%20signs%20of%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Tennant%2C%20the%20deputy%20director%20of%20a%20firm%20that%20provides%20liability%20insurance%20for%20nearly%20100%20New%20Jersey%20school%20districts%2C%20told%20me%20that%20training%20for%20reporting%20suspected%20abuse%20needed%20to%20be%20improved.%20Teachers%2C%20he%20said%2C%20are%20often%20encouraged%20to%20go%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20help%20struggling%20students%2C%20and%20they%20need%20granular%20guidance%20on%20how%20not%20to%20cross%20boundaries.%20Navigating%20those%20limits%20can%20be%20especially%20challenging%20for%20young%20teachers%20in%20their%2020s%2C%20Tennant%20said%2C%20who%20sometimes%20feel%20they%20have%20more%20in%20common%20with%20their%20students%20than%20with%20their%20older%20colleagues.%20The%20students%20who%20need%20additional%20support%20from%20teachers%20are%20often%20the%20same%20ones%20who%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F30716020%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4713310%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshows%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20being%20groomed%2C%20a%20pattern%20that%20plays%20out%20again%20and%20again%20in%20the%20disciplinary%20documents%20we%20analyzed%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20educators%2C%20they%20are%20told%20all%20the%20time%2C%20'Build%20a%20relationship%20with%20your%20students%2C'%26quot%3B%20Tennant%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20schools%20there's%20an%20intimacy%20that%20doesn't%20exist%20in%20any%20other%20organization.%20You%20need%20to%20wrestle%20with%20that%2C%20talk%20about%20it%2C%20and%20be%20constantly%20aware.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20unified%20tracking%20system%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20in%20teacher%20sexual%20misconduct%20agree%20that%20one%20of%20the%20most%20critical%20steps%20in%20preventing%20abuse%20is%20for%20schools%20to%20avoid%20hiring%20documented%20predators.%20Yet%20there%20is%20no%20surefire%20way%20for%20administrators%20to%20know%20that%20someone%20they're%20considering%20for%20a%20job%20has%20a%20history%20of%20sexual%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20federal%20system%20for%20tracking%20educators%20who%20abuse%20students%2C%20NASDTEC%20has%20stepped%20into%20the%20breach.%20Since%201988%2C%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC-based%20nonprofit%20has%20maintained%20a%20clearinghouse%20of%20adverse%20actions%20taken%20against%20teacher%20credentials%20from%20all%2050%20states%20and%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia.%20But%20the%20database%20is%20not%20public%3B%20it's%20available%20only%20to%20state%20credentialing%20agencies%20and%20the%20small%20fraction%20of%20districts%20that%20opt%20in%20and%20pay%20a%20modest%20annual%20fee.%20Only%20254%20school%20districts%20across%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20less%20than%202%25%20%E2%80%94%20currently%20have%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASDTEC's%20executive%20director%2C%20Jimmy%20Adams%2C%20chalked%20up%20the%20small%20number%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20awareness%2C%20which%20he%20said%20he's%20working%20to%20address%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20his%20predecessor%2C%20Phil%20Rogers%2C%20told%20me%20that%20he'd%20often%20run%20into%20resistance%20when%20pitching%20the%20clearinghouse%20to%20superintendents.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20surprising%20how%20many%20districts%20have%20no%20interest%20in%20it.%20They%20just%20see%20it%20as%20another%20chore%2C%26quot%3B%20Rogers%20said%2C%20recalling%20efforts%20his%20staff%20made%20to%20expand%20access%20and%20redesign%20the%20online%20portal%20to%20make%20searching%20for%20teachers'%20names%20more%20straightforward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20can%20prevent%20a%20problem%20and%20you%20choose%20not%20to%2C%20it's%20just%20baffling%2C%26quot%3B%20Rogers%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20way%20to%20explain%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20records%20states%20share%20with%20NASDTEC%20are%20often%20uncategorized.%20In%20Kentucky%2C%20for%20example%2C%20state%20officials%20reported%20460%20adverse%20actions%20taken%20against%20teacher%20credentials%20from%202017%20to%202022%2C%20labeling%2010%25%20as%20having%20stemmed%20from%20sexual%20misconduct.%20But%20last%20year%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kentucky.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Feducation%2Farticle263481018.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELexington%20Herald-Leader%3C%2Fa%3E%20analyzed%20a%20subset%20of%20those%20cases%20and%20obtained%20the%20underlying%20documents%2C%20finding%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20its%20sample%20%E2%80%94%2061%25%20%E2%80%94%20related%20to%20sexual%20misconduct.%20(Toni%20Konz%20Tatman%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Kentucky's%20Department%20of%20Education%2C%20declined%20to%20say%20why%20the%20agency%20doesn't%20note%20which%20cases%20are%20sex-related%2C%20saying%20the%20agency%20reports%20all%20adverse%20actions%20to%20NASDTEC%20%26quot%3Bregardless%20of%20the%20offense.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20see%20whether%20such%20discrepancies%20are%20common%2C%20I%20requested%20the%20adverse%20actions%20on%20teacher%20credentials%20that%20each%20state%20has%20reported%20to%20NASDTEC%20since%202017.%20The%20records%2C%20which%20we%20obtained%20from%2033%20states%2C%20show%20that%20action%20was%20taken%20against%20at%20least%2022%2C000%20teacher%20credentials.%20But%20only%2011%20of%20these%20states%20disclosed%20whether%20a%20given%20incident%20was%20sex-related.%20Thousands%20of%20cases%20in%20those%20states%20appeared%20to%20involve%20misconduct%20with%20a%20student%20%E2%80%94%20with%20language%20referencing%20an%20inappropriate%20relationship%20with%20a%20minor%20or%20%26quot%3Bconduct%20unbecoming%20to%20the%20teacher%20profession%2C%26quot%3B%20among%20other%20vague%20verbiage%20%E2%80%94%20but%20state%20officials%20didn't%20file%20them%20as%20sex-related.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Oak%20Harbor%20High%20School%20in%20Oak%20Harbor%2C%20Washington%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581a4201c5c7b8c9a099aa9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOak%20Harbor%20High%20School%2C%20near%20Seattle%2C%20where%20teacher%20Mina%20K.%20Bateman%20was%20reprimanded%20for%20communicating%20inappropriately%20with%20a%20student.%20Her%20next%20school%20had%20no%20idea%20at%20the%20time%20of%20her%20hire.%3Cp%3EChona%20Kasinger%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20states%20claimed%20that%20they%20didn't%20maintain%20a%20record%20of%20what%20they'd%20sent%20NASDTEC%2C%20or%20heavily%20redacted%20their%20reports%20before%20releasing%20them.%20Louisiana's%20Department%20of%20Education%2C%20for%20example%2C%20initially%20gave%20me%20a%20spreadsheet%20including%20columns%20for%20each%20type%20of%20misconduct%20%3Cem%3Eexcept%3C%2Fem%3E%20sexual%20misconduct.%20I%20pressed%20for%20an%20explanation%2C%20struggling%20to%20see%20how%20the%20omission%20could%20be%20inadvertent.%20Eventually%20the%20department%20released%20an%20unredacted%20version%2C%20showing%20at%20least%2018%20credential%20revocations%20for%20sexual%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20transparency%20sometimes%20extends%20to%20what%20districts%20disclose%20to%20their%20own%20state%20licensing%20boards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20try%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20to%20get%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kris%20Murakami%2C%20a%20licensing%20specialist%20with%20the%20Hawaii%20Teacher%20Standards%20Board%2C%20which%20oversees%20credentials%20for%20the%20state's%2013%2C000%20teachers.%20Murakami%20said%20her%20office%20isn't%20notified%20by%20the%20state's%20largest%20school%20district%2C%20which%20employs%20the%20majority%20of%20teachers%20on%20the%20island%2C%20when%20a%20teacher%20is%20investigated%20for%20suspected%20abuse.%20When%20an%20investigation%20ends%20in%20a%20teacher's%20resignation%20or%20termination%2C%20the%20district%20doesn't%20routinely%20share%20disciplinary%20records%20with%20her%20office%20in%20a%20timely%20manner%2C%20she%20said%20%E2%80%94%20records%20she%20needs%20to%20take%20action%20against%20a%20teacher's%20license.%20She%20sometimes%20learns%20about%20abuse%20from%20local%20news%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20concern%20is%20that%20without%20knowledge%20that%20individuals%20were%20disciplined%2C%20we%20have%20no%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20Murakami%20said.%20%26quot%3BTherefore%2C%20some%20teachers%20could%20still%20be%20in%20the%20classroom%26quot%3B%20in%20one%20of%20Hawaii's%20charter%20or%20private%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20Murakami's%20boss%2C%20the%20board's%20executive%20director%2C%20Felicia%20Villalobos%2C%20why%20she%20thought%20the%20district%20wasn't%20more%20transparent.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20the%20individual%20is%20terminated%2C%20they%20couldn't%20care%20less%20about%20the%20license%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%2C%20'We%20got%20rid%20of%20this%20person.%20That's%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20pattern%20I'd%20noticed%20in%20the%20data%3A%20teachers%20being%20disciplined%20at%20the%20district%20level%20but%20retaining%20their%20state%20credential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(A%20district%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20make%20anyone%20available%20for%20an%20interview%20and%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20detailed%20written%20queries.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20state%20credentialing%20agencies%20have%20chosen%20transparency%2C%20creating%20online%20portals%20where%20anyone%20can%20search%20a%20teacher's%20name%20to%20see%20whether%20they%20are%20credentialed.%20But%20few%20disclose%20why%20a%20credential%20was%20revoked%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20opening%20the%20door%20for%20disgraced%20teachers%20to%20pack%20their%20bags%20and%20find%20a%20job%20in%20one%20of%20the%20many%20states%20facing%20a%20crushing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteacher-shortage-schools-nurses-daycare-costs-inflation-rate-retail-workers-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteacher%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20records%20show%2C%20Anthony%20Rudy%20Cisneros%2C%20a%20teacher%20in%20the%20Santa%20Fe%20Public%20Schools%20in%20New%20Mexico%2C%20repeatedly%20messaged%20a%2017-year-old%20student%20asking%20for%20photos%20of%20her.%20%26quot%3BMe%20being%20a%20creeper%20asking%20you%20for%20a%20sexy%20picture!%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20to%20her.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20a%20very%20beautiful%20young%20lady!%26quot%3B%20A%20couple%20of%20months%20after%2C%20the%20district's%20superintendent%20sent%20Cisneros%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233976-teacher-anthony-rudy-cisneros-notice-of-termination%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enotice%20of%20termination%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20informing%20him%20that%20the%20reasons%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233975-teacher-anthony-rudy-cisneros-notice-of-termination-for-sexual-harassment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshall%20not%20be%20publicly%20disclosed%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20When%20I%20asked%20him%20about%20the%20misconduct%2C%20Cisneros%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWho%20gives%20a%20fuck%3F%20I%20can%20care%20less.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Santa%20Fe%20Public%20Schools%20spokesperson%2C%20Cody%20Dynarski%2C%20said%20that%20in%20cases%20like%20Cisneros'%2C%20the%20reason%20for%20termination%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20disclosed%20to%20another%20school%20district%20upon%20inquiry%20so%20that%20we%20do%20not%20pass%20a%20problem%20from%20one%20school%20district%20to%20another.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20New%20Mexico%20Public%20Education%20Department's%20online%20portal%20offers%20only%20a%20one-word%20description%20of%20Cisneros'%20credential%20status%3A%20%26quot%3Brevoked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECursory%20investigations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20a%20former%20student%20of%20a%20stage%20manager%2C%20Jacob%20Zamora%2C%20shared%20his%20experience%20with%20a%20psychologist%2C%20it%20had%20been%20nine%20years%20since%20Zamora%20began%20having%20sex%20with%20him.%20He%20had%20been%20depressed%2C%20the%20young%20man%20told%20police%2C%20and%20Zamora%2C%20then%20his%20teacher%2C%20was%20the%20only%20adult%20he%20could%20confide%20in%20at%20the%20time.%20The%20day%20Zamora%20performed%20oral%20sex%20on%20him%20in%20his%20bedroom%20was%20the%20first%20sexual%20experience%20of%20his%20life%3B%20after%20that%2C%20Zamora%20met%20with%20him%20for%20sex%20%26quot%3Bevery%20other%20weekend%26quot%3B%20for%20months%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20alerted%20Zamora's%20employer%2C%20Arizona's%20Skyline%20High%20School%2C%20in%20June%202021%20and%20later%20shared%20documents.%20Yet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233978-mesa-public-schools-file-from-investigation-of-sexual-abuse-by-teacher-jacob-zamora%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edistrict%20records%20indicate%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20head%20of%20HR%2C%20Renee%20Parker%2C%20waited%20until%20August%2028%20of%20that%20year%20to%20investigate%20%E2%80%94%20three%20weeks%20after%20school%20had%20started.%20Parker's%20notes%20show%20that%20her%20investigation%20amounted%20to%20a%20single%20meeting%20with%20Zamora.%20She%20asked%20him%20repeatedly%20about%20meeting%20up%20with%20students%20outside%20school%2C%20and%20he%20said%20he%20did%20so%20often%2C%20in%20groups.%20%26quot%3BI%20provided%20coaching%20telling%20him%20that%20it%20was%20time%20to%20stop%20meeting%20students%20off%20of%20campus%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233978-mesa-public-schools-file-from-investigation-of-sexual-abuse-by-teacher-jacob-zamora%23document%2Fp1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Skyline%20High%20School%20in%20Mesa%2C%20Arizona%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580ac8450edbc52a86565c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPolice%20alerted%20Skyline%20High%20School%20in%20Mesa%2C%20Arizona%2C%20that%20one%20of%20their%20teachers%2C%20Jacob%20Zamora%2C%20was%20under%20investigation.%20The%20district%20waited%20two%20months%20to%20call%20him%20in%20for%20an%20interview.%3Cp%3EMatt%20Williams%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDays%20after%20Parker%20questioned%20him%2C%20Zamora%20was%20arrested%20and%20charged%20with%20three%20counts%20of%20sexual%20contact%20with%20a%20minor.%20The%20following%20week%2C%20he%20sat%20down%20with%20Parker%20for%20a%20due-process%20hearing.%20This%20time%2C%20Zamora%20admitted%20to%20a%20sexual%20relationship%20with%20the%20boy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20made%20another%20startling%20admission%3A%20He'd%20sexually%20abused%20several%20more%20students.%20%26quot%3BI%20pressed%20for%20names%20of%20the%20victims%20multiple%20times%2C%20but%20he%20would%20just%20say%20that%20he%20did%20not%20remember%20them%20by%20name%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20wrote.%20She%20told%20him%20she%20would%20recommend%20that%20he%20be%20fired%2C%20and%20noted%20that%20Zamora%20%26quot%3Baccepted%20resignation%20in%20lieu%20of%20termination.%26quot%3B%20There's%20no%20record%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233978-mesa-public-schools-file-from-investigation-of-sexual-abuse-by-teacher-jacob-zamora%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20files%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Parker%20interviewed%20any%20other%20teacher%20or%20student%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20identify%20Zamora's%20additional%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZamora%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20sexual%20conduct%20with%20a%20minor%20in%202022%20and%20was%20sentenced%20to%20five%20years%20in%20prison%3B%20he%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20A%20district%20spokesperson%2C%20Jen%20Snyder%2C%20said%20Parker%20%26quot%3Bworked%20directly%20with%20the%20Mesa%20Police%20Department%20and%20followed%20their%20guidance%26quot%3B%20in%20conducting%20her%20investigation%20of%20Zamora.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20388%20disciplinary%20files%20related%20to%20sexual%20misconduct%20we%20obtained%2C%20less%20than%20half%20contain%20evidence%20that%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20was%20conducted.%20Most%20of%20the%20disciplinary%20files%20show%20that%20administrators%20simply%20interviewed%20the%20teacher%2C%20or%20the%20teacher%20and%20the%20student%20they%20were%20accused%20of%20abusing.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20as%20with%20Parker's%20first%20interview%20with%20Zamora%2C%20administrators%20then%20allowed%20the%20educator%20back%20into%20the%20classroom%20with%20a%20warning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Gibbs%20High%20School%20in%20St.%20Petersburg%2C%20Florida%2C%20an%20anonymous%20tipster%20reported%20in%202018%20that%20a%20coach%20was%20having%20an%20%26quot%3Binappropriate%20relationship%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20student.%20Principal%20Reuben%20Hepburn%2C%20who%20has%20since%20died%2C%20spoke%20with%20the%20child's%20father%2C%20who%2C%20according%20to%20notes%20of%20the%20meeting%2C%20told%20him%20the%20coach%20was%20%26quot%3Bvery%20involved%20with%20his%203%20children%20%E2%80%94%20with%20his%20blessing.%26quot%3B%20Maybe%20the%20tip%20about%20the%20coach%20was%20false%2C%20or%20maybe%20it%20wasn't.%20Hepburn%20never%20found%20out%2C%20because%20the%20investigation%20ended%20there%2C%20with%20a%20note%20that%20he%20would%20monitor%20the%20teacher%20and%20concluding%3A%20%26quot%3BFile%20under%20school%20name%3A%20unsubstantiated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22637%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20summary%20of%20an%20investigation%20that%20a%20principal%20conducted%20after%20an%20anonymous%20complaint%20that%20a%20coach%20in%20Florida%20had%20an%20inappropriate%20relationship%20with%20a%20student.%5CnCredit%3A%20Pinellas%20County%20Schools%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581db7e1c5c7b8c9a09ca45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22424%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20principal%20in%20St.%20Petersburg%2C%20Florida%2C%20received%20a%20tip%20in%202018%20that%20a%20coach%20was%20sexually%20involved%20with%20a%20student.%20After%20a%20single%20conversation%20with%20the%20student's%20father%2C%20he%20labeled%20the%20allegation%20%26quot%3Bunsubstantiated.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EPinellas%20County%20Schools%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Clayton%20County%2C%20Georgia%2C%20a%20district%20HR%20official%20reprimanded%20a%20teacher%20named%20William%20Zerressen%20in%202022%20after%20a%20complaint%20alleged%20that%20he'd%20hugged%20a%20grade-school%20student%20and%20touched%20her%20%26quot%3Bin%20a%20way%20that%20made%20her%20feel%20uncomfortable.%26quot%3B%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233980-teacher-william-zerressen-sexual-misconduct-investigative-notes-clayton-county-schools%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereprimand%3C%2Fa%3E%20itemizes%20eight%20previous%20allegations%20spanning%20two%20decades%2C%20noting%20the%20%26quot%3Bsimilarity%20and%20the%20severity%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20misconduct.%20It%20then%20instructs%20Zerressen%20to%20engage%20in%20%26quot%3Bappropriate%20student%20interactions%2C%26quot%3B%20attaches%20a%20set%20of%20employee%20policies%2C%20and%20allows%20him%20to%20continue%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20indication%20that%20the%20official%20interviewed%20any%20of%20the%20other%20complainants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZerressen%20told%20me%20that%20administrators%20removed%20the%20student%20from%20his%20class%20and%20that%20an%20investigation%20found%20no%20wrongdoing.%20He%20also%20said%20he's%20now%20retired%20and%20suggested%20that%20the%20string%20of%20misconduct%20complaints%20over%20the%20course%20of%20his%20career%20were%20fabricated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMild%20sanctions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disciplinary%20documents%20show%20that%20substantiated%20misconduct%20by%20teachers%20often%20leads%20to%20minor%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20case%2C%20the%20Lake%20Washington%20School%20District%20in%20Washington%20State%20identified%20a%20%26quot%3Bpattern%20of%20inappropriate%20behavior%26quot%3B%20by%20Scott%20Nelson%2C%20a%20PE%20teacher%2C%20including%20complaints%20from%20students%20that%20resulted%20in%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233982-lake-washington-school-district-file-on-sexual-misconduct-investigations-of-teacher-scott-nelson%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix%20separate%20investigations%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20a%20nearly%2030-year%20career.%20Students%20accused%20Nelson%20of%20making%20sexist%20comments%20that%20made%20them%20uncomfortable%20and%20said%20he'd%20%26quot%3Bpoked%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bgrabbed%26quot%3B%20them.%20He%20was%20repeatedly%20warned%20that%20%26quot%3Btouch%20was%20only%20to%20be%20used%20when%20necessary%20for%20health%20and%20safety%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20placed%20on%20administrative%