er-coach-groomed-sexual-assault-victim-for-years%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20suspicions%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20Ladd's%20relationship%20with%20a%20female%20student.%20Once%20at%20his%20new%20job%2C%20Ladd%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24234003-teacher-paul-ladd-termination-notice-following-sexual-abuse-charges-vermont%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earrested%20and%20charged%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20sexually%20assaulting%20the%20girl.%20Missisquoi's%20superintendent%2C%20Julie%20Regimbal%2C%20told%20me%20she'd%20been%20blindsided%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20district%20had%20made%20three%20reference%20checks%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bthere%20were%20no%20concerns%20or%20allegations%20of%20misconduct%20of%20any%20kind%20shared.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(Ladd%20was%20eventually%20convicted%20of%20sexual%20assault%20and%20sentenced%20to%20a%20year%20in%20prison%3B%20he%20did%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20Lynn%20Cota%2C%20the%20superintendent%20for%20his%20previous%20district%2C%20Franklin%20Northeast%20Supervisory%20Union%2C%20said%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20aware%20of%20any%20sexual%20misconduct%20by%20Mr.%20Ladd%20while%20he%20was%20employed%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20district.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20Neal%2C%20the%20public-safety%20teacher%20in%20West%20Virginia%20who%20urged%20the%20student%20he%20abused%20to%20%26quot%3Bdeny%20it%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20also%20had%20a%20history%20his%20employers%20at%20the%20Putnam%20Career%20and%20Technical%20Center%20were%20unaware%20of.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233972-putnam-county-schools-notes-file-for-sexual-abuse-by-teacher-kevin-dean-neal%23document%2Fp25%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDocuments%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20that%20a%20student's%20mother%20at%20one%20point%20confronted%20Putnam's%20principal%20about%20Neal's%20background%20at%20Ben%20Franklin%20Career%20Center%2C%20a%20nearby%20technical%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Putnam%20principal%2C%20CD%20Caldwell%2C%20sent%20an%20urgent%20email%20to%20a%20staffer%20at%20Ben%20Franklin%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20had%20told%20me%20initially%20there%20were%20unfounded%20allegations%26quot%3B%20against%20Neal.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20very%20disturbed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20went%20on%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20you%20started%20filling%20me%20in%20with%20all%20you%20knew%20about%20Ben%20Franklin%20and%20the%20accusations%20there.%26quot%3B%20Caldwell%20mentioned%20his%20conversation%20with%20the%20mother.%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20her%20I%20could%20not%20talk%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20(Briana%20Warner%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Kanawha%20County%20Schools%2C%20which%20oversees%20Ben%20Franklin%2C%20said%20while%20Putnam%20could%20have%20asked%20for%20Neal's%20personnel%20file%20during%20the%20hiring%20process%2C%20%26quot%3Bto%20our%20knowledge%2C%20that%20was%20not%20requested.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeal%20was%20eventually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wvgazettemail.com%2Fnews%2Flegal_affairs%2Fformer-putnam-law-enforcement-teacher-arrested-on-felony-sexual-abuse-solicitation-charges%2Farticle_429353e8-d245-5232-ab3a-1046504ff2ea.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econvicted%20of%20sexual%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20potentially%20preventable%20misconduct%20at%20Putnam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20letter%20from%20a%20student%20to%20administrators%20disclosing%20that%20they%20knew%20about%20a%20classmate's%20sexual%20relationship%20with%20a%20teacher.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581dc8ba79e5746976b0b7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22548%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFew%20districts%20train%20students%20on%20what%20to%20do%20if%20they%20witness%20teacher%20sexual%20misconduct.%20When%20a%20student%20in%20Putnam%20County%2C%20West%20Virginia%2C%20reported%20that%20teacher%20Kevin%20Neal%20was%20having%20sex%20with%20a%20classmate%2C%20she%20said%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bconfused%20on%20the%20whole%20situation%26quot%3B%20and%20debated%20whether%20to%20alert%20an%20adult.%3Cp%3EPutnam%20County%20Schools%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20federal%20Department%20of%20Education%20published%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foese.ed.gov%2Ffiles%2F2022%2F06%2FStudy-of-State-Policies-to-Prohibit-Aiding-and-Abetting-Sexual-Misconduct-in-Schools.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20explosive%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20detailed%20the%20fragmented%20and%20inadequate%20state-by-state%20approach%20to%20preventing%20abusive%20teachers%20from%20reoffending.%20The%20report%20found%20that%2016%20states%20lacked%20any%20so-called%20Pass%20the%20Trash%20bans%2C%20a%20collection%20of%20laws%20requiring%20districts%20to%20disclose%20sexual-misconduct%20allegations%20against%20teachers%20to%20prospective%20future%20employers%20or%20to%20look%20into%20applicants'%20employment%20histories.%20Yet%20the%20report%20withheld%20the%20names%20of%20states%20to%20%26quot%3Bmaintain%20their%20anonymity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20obtained%20the%20report's%20underlying%20data%2C%20which%20allowed%20us%20to%20identify%20which%20states%20have%20instituted%20a%20variety%20of%20laws%20and%20policies%20meant%20to%20prevent%20districts%20from%20hiring%20teachers%20who%20have%20engaged%20in%20sexual%20misconduct%20or%20from%20suppressing%20information%20about%20their%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20out%20that%20West%20Virginia%2C%20home%20to%20Putnam%20County%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%2016%20states%20that%20does%20only%20the%20minimum%20%E2%80%94%20requiring%20a%20criminal%20background%20check%20for%20new%20hires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FWPcFw%2F7%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%2221%20states%20lack%20robust%20laws%20to%20prevent%20%26quot%3Bpassing%20the%20trash%26quot%3B%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22632%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EDocuments%20show%20that%20even%20districts%20in%20states%20with%20the%20strongest%20combination%20of%20Pass%20the%20Trash%20laws%20don't%20always%20comply%20with%20them.%20When%20Mina%20K.%20Bateman%20was%20hired%20as%20a%20special-education%20assistant%20in%20Seattle%20Public%20Schools%20in%20late%202017%2C%20she%20failed%20to%20disclose%20a%202016%20reprimand%20stemming%20from%20inappropriate%20conduct%20with%20a%20student%20at%20her%20previous%20district%2C%20nearby%20Oak%20Harbor.%20Seattle%20Public%20Schools%20should%20have%20requested%20Bateman's%20records%20prior%20to%20hiring%20her%2C%20as%20required%20under%20Washington's%20Pass%20the%20Trash%20law%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20of%20its%20kind%2C%20enacted%20back%20in%202004.%20But%20Seattle%20didn't%20ask%20Oak%20Harbor%20to%20share%20the%20disciplinary%20documents%20until%202018%2C%20when%20it%20sent%20a%20state%20sexual-misconduct%20disclosure%20release%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20Bateman's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24234004-seattle-public-schools-last-chance-agreement-and-disciplinary-documents-for-teacher-mina-k-bateman-from-oak-harbor%23document%2Fp4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereprimand%3C%2Fa%3E%20surfaced%20%E2%80%94%20a%20substantiated%20allegation%20that%20she%20had%20messaged%20a%20male%20student%20on%20Facebook%20and%20communicated%20inappropriately%20with%20him%2C%20violating%20a%20policy%20on%20%26quot%3Bmaintaining%20professional%20staff%2Fstudent%20boundaries%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20district%20administrators%20allowed%20her%20to%20continue%20teaching%20under%20a%20%26quot%3Blast%20chance%26quot%3B%20agreement%20and%20did%20not%20require%20her%20to%20admit%20to%20any%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBateman%20continued%20teaching%20in%20Seattle%20until%20August%202019%3B%20she%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20(Bev%20Redmond%2C%20a%20Seattle%20Public%20Schools%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20district%20had%20since%20%26quot%3Btightened%20its%20application%20standards%20and%20would%20currently%20not%20allow%20an%20employee%20who%20provided%20false%20information%20on%20a%20job%20application%20to%20remain%20employed.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Pass%20the%20Trash%20laws%20generally%20require%20information-sharing%20among%20district%20administrators%2C%20they%20stop%20short%20of%20requiring%20that%20this%20information%20be%20made%20publicly%20available%2C%20leaving%20students%20and%20parents%20in%20the%20dark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20state%20laws%2C%20the%20federal%20Every%20Student%20Succeeds%20Act%20of%202015%20requires%20any%20educational%20institution%20receiving%20federal%20funds%20to%20have%20policies%20that%20prohibit%20employees%20from%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.everystudentsucceedsact.org%2Fcopy-of-copy-of-copy-of-copy-of-copy-of-copy-of-copy-of-copy-of-copy-of-copy-of-title-vlll-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaiding%20and%20abetting%20sexual%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20by%20assisting%20those%20who%20engaged%20in%20sexual%20misconduct%20in%20getting%20a%20new%20job%20elsewhere.%20Terri%20Miller%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20advocacy%20group%20Stop%20Educator%20Sexual%20Abuse%2C%20Misconduct%20and%20Exploitation%2C%20said%20that%20law%2C%20too%2C%20is%20not%20always%20enforced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20have%20teeth%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20say%20states%20can%20lose%20federal%20funding%20for%20not%20following%20this%2C%20but%20not%20a%20single%20state%20has.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20expensive%20and%20time-consuming%20to%20fire%20a%20teacher%2C%20Miller%20said%2C%20between%20legal%20costs%20and%20negotiations%20with%20teachers%20union%20reps.%20But%20failing%20to%20conduct%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20and%20allowing%20teachers%20to%20resign%20effectively%20evades%20disclosure%20laws%20and%20%26quot%3Bexacerbates%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%20explained.%20%26quot%3BThe%20teacher%20goes%20on%2C%20and%20offends%20at%20their%20next%20school.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnforced%20secrecy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20national%20conversation%20has%20erupted%20in%20recent%20years%20about%20the%20ethics%20of%20nondisclosure%20agreements%20in%20cases%20of%20sexual%20misconduct%20in%20the%20workplace.%20Last%20year%2C%20Congress%20responded%20by%20passing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2F117%2Fplaws%2Fpubl224%2FPLAW-117publ224.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpeak%20Out%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20bans%20the%20use%20of%20NDAs%20to%20gag%20victims%20of%20sexual%20abuse.%20But%20this%20legislative%20urgency%20hasn't%20extended%20to%20schools.%20Only%2020%20states%20have%20enacted%20laws%20or%20policies%20that%20prohibit%20district%20officials%20from%20suppressing%20information%20about%20sexual%20misconduct%20by%20school%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20that%20nondisclosure%20clauses%20remain%20routine%20in%20school-district%20severance%20agreements%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20some%20of%20the%20states%20that%20prohibit%20them%20in%20cases%20of%20sexual%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20more%20than%203%2C700%20such%20agreements%20we%20obtained%20from%20school%20districts%20since%202017%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20offer%20no%20detail%20of%20the%20conduct%20that%20led%20to%20the%20departure.%20But%20in%20196%20cases%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20pair%20the%20agreements%20with%20disciplinary%20records%20released%20by%20the%20same%20district.%20We%20found%20that%20districts%20in%2013%20states%20%E2%80%94%20Arizona%2C%20California%2C%20Florida%2C%20Kansas%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20Michigan%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20Washington%2C%20Wisconsin%2C%20and%20Wyoming%20%E2%80%94%20used%20NDAs%20to%20gag%20district%20officials%20from%20speaking%20about%20allegations%20of%20teacher%20sexual%20misconduct%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20the%20claims%20were%20substantiated.%20Of%20those%2C%20four%20states%20%E2%80%94%20Florida%2C%20Michigan%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20Washington%20%E2%80%94%20explicitly%20prohibit%20the%20use%20of%20NDAs%20by%20districts%20to%20conceal%20sexual%20misconduct%20by%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nondisclosure%20clauses%20often%20bar%20school%20officials%20from%20sharing%20anything%20beyond%20basic%20information%20with%20prospective%20employers%2C%20such%20as%20dates%20of%20employment%20and%20subjects%20taught.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20use%20of%20NDAs%2C%20many%20districts%20are%20bound%20by%20union%20contracts%20to%20keep%20teachers'%20personnel%20files%20private.%20Nearly%20a%20third%20of%20union%20contracts%20feature%20such%20protections%2C%20according%20to%20our%20analysis%20of%20142%20union%20contracts%20from%20large%20districts%20in%20every%20state%2C%20shared%20with%20us%20by%20the%20National%20Council%20on%20Teacher%20Quality%2C%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC-based%20think%20tank.%20This%20kind%20of%20contract%20language%20was%20often%20cited%20by%20administrators%20in%20response%20to%20our%20requests%20for%20disciplinary%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20simple%20secrecy%20mechanisms%20play%20a%20major%20role%20in%20allowing%20predatory%20teachers%20back%20in%20the%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESESAME%2C%20the%20organization%20led%20by%20Miller%2C%20has%20worked%20with%20state%20and%20federal%20lawmakers%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20ban%20NDAs%20in%20school%20district%20severance%20agreements.%20But%20she%20said%20SESAME%20had%20run%20into%20opposition%20from%20teacher%20unions.%20While%20Pass%20the%20Trash%20laws%20in%20many%20states%20require%20that%20past%20misconduct%20findings%20be%20disclosed%2C%20compliance%20is%20difficult%2C%20Miller%20said%2C%20as%20the%20culture%20of%20many%20school%20districts%20is%20%26quot%3Bingrained%20in%20silence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20culture%20I%20often%20encountered%20while%20I%20sought%20teacher%20disciplinary%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Montana's%20rural%20Lockwood%20School%20District%2C%20Superintendent%20Tobin%20Novasio%20initially%20redacted%20the%20name%20of%20Lynette%20Larson%2C%20a%20deceased%20teacher%2C%20from%20what%20he%20told%20me%20was%20the%20district's%20only%20recent%20separation%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20likely%20don't%20have%20a%20legal%20leg%20to%20stand%20on%2C%20I'm%20just%20unsure%20what%20value%20there%20is%20in%20releasing%20Lynette's%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20Novasio%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24234000-lockwood-schools-tobin-novasio-emails-about-business-insider-reporter-matt-dranges-public-records-request-for-teacher-disciplinary-records%23document%2Fp7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemailed%20a%20colleague%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sure%20they%20are%20looking%20to%20do%20an%20article%20on%20how%20many%20misconduct%20cases%20there%20have%20been%20and%20how%20much%20taxpayer%20money%20is%20wasted%20on%20these%20buyouts%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20another.%20%26quot%3BIn%20our%20case%20it%20was%20much%20more%20cost%20efficient%20to%20pay%20her%20insurance%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20than%20hire%20an%20attorney%20to%20terminate%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20administrators%20appeared%20to%20be%20more%20concerned%20with%20avoiding%20teacher%20lawsuits%20than%20protecting%20their%20students.%20Take%20the%20Central%20Bucks%20School%20District%20outside%20Philadelphia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20something%20of%20this%20nature%2C%20the%20potential%20liability%20of%20disclosing%20this%20information%20far%20outweighs%20the%20benefits%20to%20disclosure%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20district's%20outside%20attorney%2C%20Robert%20Iannozzi%2C%20told%20me%2C%20after%20acknowledging%20that%20the%20district%20had%20discretion%20under%20the%20law%20to%20release%20teachers'%20disciplinary%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20spokesperson%20on%20the%20call%20interjected%2C%20Iannozzi%20walked%20back%20his%20remarks.%20%26quot%3BForget%20my%20concerns%20of%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20should%20not%20have%20complicated%20the%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22627%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Police%20investigative%20notes%20from%20an%20interview%20with%20a%20student%20who%20said%20that%20teacher%20Jason%20Herrington%20had%20sex%20with%20him%20at%20school%3B%20the%20student%20blamed%20himself%20for%20not%20disclosing%20this%20sooner.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658356fe1c5c7b8c9a0aa2f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22127%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20Florida's%20Pinellas%20County%20Schools%2C%20a%20former%20student%20told%20the%20police%20that%20a%20dance%20teacher%2C%20Jason%20Hall%20Herrington%2C%20had%20sex%20with%20him%20while%20he%20was%20a%20minor.%20The%20student%20said%20Herrington%20told%20him%20that%20if%20he%20reported%20the%20abuse%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20would%20not%20believe%20him%20and%20he%20would%20go%20to%20jail.%26quot%3B%20(Herrington%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.)%3Cp%3EPinellas%20County%20Schools%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20analysis%20of%20settlement%20payouts%20tracked%20by%20United%20Educators%2C%20an%20insurance%20firm%20in%20Bethesda%2C%20Maryland%2C%20shows%20that%20teachers%20don't%20represent%20the%20only%20litigation%20risk.%20Since%202017%2C%20%24886%20million%20in%20settlement%20payouts%20have%20been%20made%20across%20the%20country%20to%20students%20who%20filed%20lawsuits%20alleging%20teacher%20sexual%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bvast%20majority%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20nation's%203.5%20million%20public-school%20teachers%20%26quot%3Bare%20ethical%20professionals%20who%20work%20to%20protect%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20Adams%2C%20NASDTEC's%20director%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20agree%20that%20one%20incident%20is%20too%20many.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20cost%20of%20silence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inability%20of%20administrators%20to%20even%20determine%20how%20many%20of%20their%20teachers%20have%20been%20investigated%20for%20misconduct%20leaves%20a%20gaping%20hole%20in%20our%20understanding%20of%20sexual%20abuse%20in%20schools.%20Experts%20say%20the%20lack%20of%20data%20on%20basic%20questions%2C%20such%20as%20how%20often%20abusive%20teachers%20are%20passed%20along%20to%20other%20schools%2C%20allows%20policymakers%20and%20education%20officials%20alike%20to%20believe%20the%20problem%20isn't%20as%20widespread%20as%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20all%20about%20protecting%20the%20institution%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Amos%20Guiora%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Utah%20who%20has%20authored%20research%20papers%20on%20child%20sexual%20abuse.%20%26quot%3BSo%20that%20when%20there's%20one%20case%20that%20comes%20out%2C%20they%20can%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20that's%20just%20one%20case.'%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22West%20High%20School%20in%20Salt%20Lake%20City%2C%20Utah%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580ad161c5c7b8c9a0968c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWest%20High%20School%20in%20Salt%20Lake%20City%2C%20Utah%2C%20where%20a%20teacher%2C%20Sterrett%20Oney%20Neale%2C%20comforted%20a%20student%20after%20she%20was%20abused%20by%20a%20teacher%20at%20summer%20camp.%20Neale%20then%20groomed%20her%20for%20sex.%3Cp%3EKim%20Raff%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20invisibility%20and%20silence%20surrounding%20abuse%20in%20schools%20has%20been%20critical%20in%20allowing%20it%20to%20endure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20silence%20begins%20with%20the%20failure%20to%20itemize%20and%20prohibit%20grooming%20behaviors%20in%20educator%20codes%20of%20conduct.%20It%20continues%20when%20school%20officials%20make%20a%20problem%20quietly%20go%20away%20with%20a%20resignation%2C%20forgoing%20the%20kind%20of%20investigation%20that%20could%20uncover%20other%20victims%20and%20create%20a%20paper%20trail.%20And%20it%20is%20at%20its%20most%20dangerous%20when%20school%20officials%20decline%20to%20share%20misconduct%20allegations%20and%20even%20substantiated%20cases%20of%20abuse%20with%20an%20educator's%20next%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20set%20out%20to%20see%20whether%20these%20painfully%20obvious%20shortcomings%2C%20so%20routine%20at%20my%20alma%20mater%2C%20were%20common%20elsewhere%2C%20I%20wondered%20what%20patterns%20might%20emerge.%20Such%20as%20whether%20schools%20in%20working-class%20neighborhoods%20like%20the%20one%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20harbor%20predators.%20Or%20whether%20districts%20where%20a%20teacher%20had%20been%20arrested%20for%20sexual%20misconduct%20implemented%20changes%20or%20simply%20allowed%20history%20to%20repeat%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20I%20found%20prevention%20failures%20and%20mishandled%20allegations%20all%20across%20the%20country%2C%20in%20rich%20districts%20and%20poor%20ones%2C%20urban%20and%20rural%2C%20in%20schools%20with%20mostly%20white%20students%20and%20in%20schools%20attended%20mostly%20by%20students%20of%20color.%20In%20district%20after%20district%2C%20the%20incidents%20were%20deliberately%20shrouded%20by%20secrecy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20silence%20surrounded%20the%20case%20of%20Troy%20Pickens%2C%20the%20chorus%20teacher%20who%20was%20investigated%20in%202015%20for%20abusing%20a%20student%20at%20Neal%20Middle%20School%20in%20Durham%20County%2C%20North%20Carolina.%20%26quot%3BThe%20situation%20looked%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20HR%20official%20told%20Pickens%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24233964-civil-suit-against-wake-county-and-durham-county-schools-in-case-of-troy-logan-pickens%23document%2Fp13%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubsequent%20civil%20suit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20they%20would%20rather%20he%20resign%20than%20be%20fired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22541%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20lawsuit%20filed%20by%20the%20victim%20of%20Troy%20Pickens%20describes%20how%20the%20former%20teacher%20appears%20to%20have%20groomed%20students%20for%20sexual%20relationships.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581dcbca79e5746976b0b9f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22297%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20school%20after%20school%2C%20teachers%20used%20their%20popularity%20to%20violate%20teacher-student%20boundaries.%20Troy%20Pickens%2C%20the%20North%20Carolina%20teacher%2C%20was%20seen%20as%20%26quot%3Bcool%26quot%3B%20even%20as%20he%20touched%20female%20students%20inappropriately%2C%20according%20to%20a%202021%20lawsuit.%3Cp%3EWake%20County%20Schools%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20quiet%20resignation%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20Pickens%20to%20lie%20to%20school%20officials%20in%20nearby%20Wake%20County%20when%20he%20applied%20for%20a%20teaching%20job%20there%2C%20saying%20he'd%20left%20Neal%20to%20care%20for%20a%20sick%20family%20member.%20There%2C%20at%20Durant%20Road%20Middle%20School%2C%20Pickens%20repeatedly%20sexually%20assaulted%20a%20sixth%20grader%20in%20the%20school%20bathroom%2C%20her%20civil%20complaint%20alleges.%20(The%20suit%20settled%20out%20of%20court.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPickens%20was%20eventually%20convicted%20of%20statutory%20rape%20and%20other%20sexual%20offenses%20and%20sentenced%20to%20more%20than%2075%20years%20in%20prison.%20His%20attorney%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Durant%20Road%20Middle%20School%20in%20Raleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580933250edbc52a8655772%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221665%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDurant%20Road%20Middle%20School%20in%20Raleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina.%20Troy%20Pickens%20landed%20a%20job%20at%20Durant%20after%20being%20allowed%20to%20quietly%20resign%20from%20his%20previous%20district%3B%20he%20went%20on%20to%20sexually%20assault%20a%20sixth%20grader%20in%20the%20school%20bathroom.%3Cp%3EAndrea%20Bruce%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20student%2C%20she%20was%20unable%20to%20set%20foot%20on%20campus%20again%20at%20Durant%20Road.%20Then%20she%20stopped%20attending%20school%20for%20good.%20She%20became%20despondent%20and%20was%20treated%20for%20severe%20emotional%20distress%20and%20developed%20an%20eating%20disorder%20so%20severe%20that%20she%20was%20hospitalized.%20Her%20weight%2C%20at%20age%2012%2C%20dropped%20to%20just%2050%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPredators%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20lawsuit%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bare%20well%20known%20in%20the%20field%20of%20education%20to%20'go%20where%20the%20children%20are.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20cost%20of%20Durham%20County's%20silence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20K-12%20education%20reporter%3F%20Business%20Insider%20wants%20to%20share%20the%20teacher%20disciplinary%20records%2C%20separation%20agreements%2C%20and%20licensing%20sanctions%20we%20obtained%20with%20you.%20Sign%20up%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforms.gle%2FztCtpejhcuTNRjhd8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20we'll%20reach%20out.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20d