0Colorado%20judges%20by%20a%20deadline%20in%20early%20January%2C%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20name%20will%20still%20appear%20on%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Republican%20primary%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-holds-wide-lead-republican-2024-nominating-contest-reutersipsos-poll-2023-12-11%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20In%20nationwide%20polls%20Trump%20has%20been%20ahead%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20nationwide%20polls%2C%20Trump%20has%20been%20ahead%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20fellow%20Republican%20candidates%20like%20Florida%20governor%20Ron%20DeSantis%20and%20former%20South%20Carolina%20governor%20and%20UN%20ambassador%20Nikki%20Haley%2C%20usually%20by%20a%20wide%20margin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImpeachment%20no%20hindrance%20to%20presidential%20run%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20is%20the%20only%20US%20president%20to%20be%20impeached%20twice.%20In%20both%20cases%2C%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20charged%20Trump%20with%20articles%20of%20impeachment%20(in%202019%20it%20was%20abuse%20of%20power%20and%20obstruction%20of%20Congress%2C%20in%202021%20it%20was%20incitement%20of%20insurrection)%2C%20but%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fdonald-trump-cleared-by-us-senate-of-inciting-capitol-riots%2Fa-56561629%5C%22%3ESenate%20acquitted%20him%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20if%20the%20Senate%2C%20the%20higher%20chamber%20of%20Congress%2C%20convicts%20a%20president%20is%20he%20or%20she%20removed%20from%20office%2C%20a%20step%20that%20comes%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdisqualification%20to%20hold%20and%20enjoy%20any%20office%20of%20honour%2C%20trust%20or%20profit%20under%20the%20United%20States%E2%80%9D%20again%2C%20as%20stipulated%20in%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20double-impeachment%20is%20no%20legal%20hindrance.%20But%20what%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fdonald-trump-faces-criminal-charges%2Fa-65192807%5C%22%3ETrump%E2%80%99s%20other%20troubles%20with%20the%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20sexual%20assault%20to%20attempting%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20election%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trials%20about%20to%20start%20against%20Trump%20in%202024%20include%20civil%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fjudge-to-trump-this-is-a-courtroom-not-a-political-rally%2Fa-67322515%5C%22%3Efraud%20trials%20related%20to%20how%20Trump%20and%20his%20sons%20ran%20the%20family%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20sexual%20assault%20and%20defamation%20trial.%20In%20the%20latter%20case%2C%20a%20jury%20had%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftrump-found-liable-in-e-jean-carroll-defamation-suit%2Fa-66741217%5C%22%3Efound%20Trump%20liable%20for%20defaming%20a%20former%20columnist%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20the%20judge%20concluding%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Ftrump-rape-trial-columnist-carroll-4974ef026f3da61bc6f1b7ddda3ad10e%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20that%20Trump%20raped%20the%20woman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat%20Trump%20raped%20the%20woman%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20then%20denied%20it.%20The%20upcoming%20trial%20is%20supposed%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20Trump%20will%20have%20to%20pay%20the%20writer%20for%20defaming%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20several%20cases%20against%20the%20former%20president%20related%20to%20his%20behaviour%20after%20losing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2F2020-us-presidential-election%2Ft-52634123%5C%22%3E2020%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20A%20federal%20criminal%20trial%20in%20Miami%20in%20which%20Trump%20is%20charged%20with%20keeping%20classified%20government%20documents%20at%20his%20Mar-a-Lago%20home%20when%20he%20was%20no%20longer%20president%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftrump-pleads-not-guilty-in-georgia-election-case%2Fa-66688221%5C%22%3Eracketeering%20trial%20in%20Georgia%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20has%20Trump%20and%2018%20other%20defendants%20charged%20with%20interfering%20with%202020%20election%20results%2C%20and%20a%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20case%20in%20which%20Trump%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fus-supreme-court-asked-to-rule-on-trump-immunity-claim%2Fa-67696189%5C%22%3Echarged%20with%20felonies%20in%20connection%20with%20his%20attempt%20to%20remain%20in%20power%20after%20losing%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20the%20outcome%20of%20these%20trials%2C%20though%2C%20Trump%20would%20not%20lose%20the%20eligibility%20to%20run%20for%20president.%20The%20US%20Constitution%20has%20no%20limits%20regarding%20criminal%20convictions%20for%20presidential%20hopefuls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20several%20arguments%20over%20whether%20a%20presidential%20candidate%20who%20is%20indicted%C2%A0or%20is%20involved%20in%20an%20on-going%20legal%20case%20should%20still%20run%20for%20office%2C%E2%80%9D%20Laura%20Merrifield%20Wilson%2C%20associate%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Indianapolis%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CBut%20those%20are%20based%20on%20morals%2C%20judgement%2C%20and%20preferences%2C%20not%20overt%20laws%20or%20procedural%20barriers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20convicted%20of%20a%20felony%20in%20the%20Mar-a-Lago%20case%2C%20Trump%20would%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20vote%20(in%20Florida%2C%20felons%20lose%20that%20right)%2C%20but%20he%20could%20still%20run%20for%20the%20highest%20office%20in%20the%20country.%20Even%20if%20he%20were%20sent%20to%20prison%2C%20it%20would%20not%20interfere%20with%20his%20candidacy.%20What%20would%20happen%20if%20Trump%20won%20the%20presidential%20election%20while%20in%20prison%2C%20however%2C%20is%20unclear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20so%20far%20removed%20from%20anything%20that%E2%80%99s%20ever%20happened%2C%E2%80%9D%20Erwin%20Chemerinsky%2C%20a%20constitutional%20law%20expert%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20just%20guessing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20%E2%80%98bolstered%E2%80%99%20by%20trials%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegally%2C%20the%20trials%20don%E2%80%99t%20hurt%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20presidential%20aspirations.%20But%20what%20about%20his%20appeal%20to%20voters%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndependents%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20turned%20off%20by%20a%20very%20salient%20conviction%20of%20Trump%2C%E2%80%9D%20Christopher%20Federico%2C%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20and%20political%20psychology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20any%20convictions%20are%20going%20to%20hurt%20him%20with%20his%20true%20base%20within%20the%20Republican%20party.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFederico%E2%80%99s%20colleague%20and%20fellow%20political%20psychologist%20Howard%20Lavine%20also%20says%20the%20criminal%20charges%20haven%E2%80%99t%20hurt%20Trump%20with%20his%20supporters%20%E2%80%95%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fdonald-trump-united-states-elections-2023-mug-shot%2Fa-66640224%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20contrary%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEach%20indictment%20seemed%20to%20bolster%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20potential%20vote-share%2C%E2%80%9D%20Lavine%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CHe%E2%80%99s%20framed%20this%20%5Bto%20his%20voters%5D%20as%20%E2%80%98They%E2%80%99re%20trying%20to%20exact%20retribution%20against%20me%20as%20a%20proxy%20for%20exacting%20retribution%20against%20you.'%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20with%20fear%20in%20a%20polarised%20US%20society%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Federico%20and%20Lavine%20say%20that%20Trump%20has%20intuitively%20been%20very%20successful%20at%20connecting%20with%20his%20voter%20base%20%E2%80%95%20whites%20without%20a%20college%20degree%20and%20conservative%20Black%20and%20Latino%20men.%20He%20makes%20them%20feel%20that%20he%E2%80%99s%20an%20outsider%20just%20like%20them%20and%20thus%20understands%20their%20anger%20and%20fear%20of%20being%20left%20behind%20by%20the%20elites%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocial%20reforms%20on%20gender%20issues%20and%20increased%20efforts%20for%20more%20equality%20and%20inclusion%20have%20fanned%20the%20flames%20of%20that%20fear%2C%20Lavine%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBeing%20heterosexual%20isn%E2%80%99t%20any%20better%20than%20not%20being%20heterosexual%2C%20being%20a%20man%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20give%20you%20quite%20the%20status%20it%20once%20did%2C%20whites%20are%20decreasing%20as%20a%20proportion%20of%20the%20American%20population%2C%20and%20we%20will%20soon%20be%20a%20country%20in%20which%20Christians%20will%20be%20the%20minority%2C%E2%80%9D%20Lavine%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20threatening%20the%20majority%20status%20of%20white%20Christian%20men.%C2%A0A%20lot%20of%20people%20feel%20like%20their%20social%20prestige%20is%20being%20decreased.%20And%20it%20appears%20Trump%20is%20able%20to%20laser-focus%20on%20these%20fears.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20core%20supporter%20base%2C%20the%20experts%20say%2C%20want%20to%20feel%20represented%20and%20seen%2C%20and%20believe%20that%20Trump%20will%20fight%20to%20bring%20them%20back%20to%20their%20former%20glory%20%E2%80%95%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fbiden-says-trump-maga-movement-threaten-democracy%2Fa-66955235%5C%22%3Emake%20America%20great%20again%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C.%20Potential%20criminal%20convictions%20don%E2%80%99t%20matter%20for%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20Trump%20supporters%20would%20turn%20their%20back%20on%20him%2C%20period%2C%E2%80%9D%20Wilson%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20remain%20steadfast%20and%20loyal%2C%20even%20if%20not%20to%20the%20man%2C%20certainly%20to%20the%20mythological%20representation%20of%20what%20he%20stands%20for.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fhow-trump-can-run-for-us-president-despite-legal-troubles%2Fa-67728170%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flogs1279.xiti.com%2Fhit.xiti%3Fs%3D531599%26s2%3D2%26p%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%3A%3Athewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26di%3D%26an%3D%26ac%3D%26x1%3D1%26x2%3D2%26x5%3Dthewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26x6%3D1%26x8%3Den-VAS-Volltexte-JavaScript-thewire.in-dwde%26x10%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703147383000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F14155328%2F1620px-Donald_Trump_39630669575.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-donald-trump-can-run-for-us-president-despite-legal-troubles%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20will%20appeal%20a%20ruling%20declaring%20him%20ineligible%20for%20primary%20ballots%20in%20Colorado%2C%20and%20his%20chances%20are%20good%20with%20the%20conservative-dominated%20US%20Supreme%20Court.%20But%20he%20faces%20several%20simultaneous%20legal%20battles.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-donald-trump-can-run-for-us-president-despite-legal-troubles%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20vows%20to%20keep%20up%20military%20pressure%20on%20the%20Philippines%20as%20territorial%20dispu