20couple%E2%80%99s%20significant%20contribution%20to%20modern%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20decades%20before%20its%20demolition%2C%20Bhide%20Wada%20stood%20as%20a%20modest%20and%20self-effacing%20structure%20to%20onlookers%20and%20people%20in%20the%20bustling%20neighbourhood.%20Bystanders%20who%20were%20oblivious%20to%20its%20historical%20significance%20may%20have%20thought%20of%20it%20as%20just%20another%20dilapidated%20building%20in%20the%20pool%20of%20many%20such%20structures%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%20that%20required%20immediate%20repair%20and%20renovation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20PMC%20identified%20this%20building%20as%20%E2%80%9Cdangerous%20and%20unsafe%E2%80%9D%20for%20everyday%20use.%20Irrespective%20of%20its%20introverted%20and%20unassuming%20appearance%20from%20the%20outside%2C%20Bhide%20Wada%20represented%20a%20significant%20chapter%20in%20the%20history%20of%20modern%20India.%20Even%20after%20the%20closure%20of%20the%20school%20founded%20by%20Jyotirao%20Phule%2C%20Bhide%20Wada%20was%20an%20important%20centre%20of%20public%20activism%20in%20the%2019%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20centuries.%20It%20frequently%20attracted%20prominent%20public%20figures%2C%20including%20Mahadev%20Govind%20Ranade%20and%20Dayanand%20Saraswati.%20Bhide%20Wada%20was%20a%20site%20that%20changed%20the%20lives%20of%20Savitribai%20and%20Jyotirao%20forever%20to%20become%20leading%20crusaders%20of%20equality%20and%20public%20education.%20Therefore%2C%20Bhide%20Wada%20cannot%20be%20simply%20forgotten%20as%20a%20monument%20of%20a%20bygone%20era%2C%20as%20it%20instrumentally%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20new%20political%20and%20cultural%20articulations%20in%20modern%20India.%20In%20a%20society%20that%20is%20overwhelmingly%20dominated%20by%20the%20practices%20of%20caste%20prejudices%2C%20caste%20discrimination%20and%20caste-based%20violence%2C%20Bhide%20Wada%20is%20a%20monument%20of%20alternative%20expression.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBhide%20Wada%2C%20owned%20by%20the%20Bhide%20family%2C%20was%20constructed%20in%20a%20thriving%20business%20district%20of%20Budhwar%20Peth%20when%20the%20Peshwas%20ruled%20Pune%20before%20their%20eventual%20defeat%20in%201818.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWada%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(cottage)-like%20structures%2C%20constructed%20in%20different%20Peths%20or%20localities%2C%20became%20a%20familiar%20sight%20across%20the%20city%20in%20the%2018%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%2019%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20centuries.%20One%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Bhide%20family%2C%20Tatyasaheb%20Bhide%2C%20a%20strong%20sympathiser%20and%20a%20friend%20of%20Jotirao%20Phule%2C%20wanted%20to%20help%20him%20set%20up%20a%20school.%20He%20was%20impressed%20by%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20passion%20and%20gave%20two%20rooms%20of%20his%20family%20cottage%20for%20the%20school%20premises.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20establishment%20of%20this%20school%20irked%20many%20traditionalists%20and%20deeply%20distressed%20Savitribai%2C%20Jyotirao%2C%20and%20their%20supporters.%20Here%2C%20Savitribai%20rose%20to%20the%20occasion%20and%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20that%20changed%20the%20course%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20educational%20activism%20in%20modern%20India.%20She%20was%20initially%20educated%20by%20Jyotirao%20and%20later%20completed%20teacher%20training%20courses%20to%20become%20a%20teacher%20and%20headmistress%20of%20the%20school%20located%20at%20Bhide%20Wada.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20the%20Bhide%20Wada%20school%20was%20a%20short-lived%20experiment%2C%20it%20created%20a%20long-lasting%20legacy.%20With%20time%2C%20the%20Phule%20couple%20established%20more%20than%2018%20schools%20across%20Pune.%20Savitribai%20and%20Jyotirao%20Phule%20became%20leading%20voices%20of%20radical%20anti-caste%20activism.%20Satyashodhak%20Samaj%2C%20founded%20by%20Jyotirao%2C%20was%20actively%20involved%20in%20voicing%20the%20grievances%20of%20the%20peasants%2C%20women%2C%20non-Brahmins%2C%20and%20the%20untouchables.%20Before%20launching%20the%20Satyashodhak%20Samaj%20in%201873%2C%20Phule%20established%20himself%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20potent%20critics%20of%20social%20conservatism%20and%20religious%20nationalism%20in%20Western%20India.%20Therefore%2C%20to%20understand%20the%20import%20of%20Phule%E2%80%99s%20activism%20and%20his%20radical%20stance%20against%20caste%20and%20patriarchy%2C%20the%20history%20of%20Bhide%20Wada%20cannot%20be%20forgotten.%20It%20set%20the%20tone%20for%20new%20voices%20of%20cultural%20expression%20that%20also%20foregrounded%20a%20new%20language%20of%20politics%20in%20modern%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21133019%2Fjyotirao-and-savitribai.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21133019%2Fjyotirao-and-savitribai.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21133019%2Fjyotirao-and-savitribai-300x213.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21133019%2Fjyotirao-and-savitribai-1024x726.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690147%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22851%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBusts%20of%20Mahatma%20Jyotirao%20Phule%20and%20Savitribai%20Phule.%20Photo%3A%20Priyanka%20bhise%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20time%2C%20the%20ownership%20of%20the%202%2C500%20sq%20ft%20Bhide%20Wada%20changed%20from%20one%20owner%20to%20the%20other%20in%20the%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century.%20We%20find%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20sale%20deed%20of%201924%20that%20mentioned%20the%20transfer%20of%20the%20land%20from%20Sadashiv%20Narayan%20Bhide%20to%20the%20Mavadikar%20family.%20Subsequently%2C%20Bhide%20Wada%20was%20sold%20in%20two%20phases%20to%20Pune-based%20Poune%20Merchants%20Co-operative%20Bank%20in%201969%20and%201972.%20In%202000%2C%20the%20bank%20requested%20a%20real%20estate%20firm%20to%20redevelop%20the%20property.%20After%20substantial%20redevelopment%2C%20the%20work%20was%20halted%20by%20a%20stay%20order%20in%202005.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20interesting%20aspect%20of%20this%20entire%20chronicle%20of%20Bhide%20Wada%20is%20how%20some%20historical%20sites%20associated%20with%20Dalit-OBC%20assertions%20have%20been%20conveniently%20forgotten%20in%20post-independence%20India.%20It%20took%20more%20than%2050%20years%20after%20independence%20for%20the%20state%20institutions%20to%20recognise%20the%20importance%20of%20Bhide%20Wada.%20In%202006%2C%20after%20continuous%20demands%20from%20different%20quarters%20across%20Maharashtra%2C%20the%20PMC%20and%20the%20state%20government%20finally%20proposed%20a%20plan%20to%20set%20up%20a%20national%20monument%20to%20commemorate%20the%20contributions%20of%20the%20Phule%20couple.%20After%2013%20years%20of%20protracted%20legal%20battle%20with%20its%20occupants%2C%20the%20site%20was%20finally%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20PMC%20through%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fpune-news%2Fhandover-bhide-wada-to-pmc-within-a-month-sc-to-owners-tenants-101698940794627.html%5C%22%3Eintervention%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20monuments%20like%20Bhide%20Wada%20are%20ignored%20highlights%20how%20histories%20of%20anti-caste%20and%20Dalit-Bahujan%20politics%20are%20still%20rendered%20unacceptable%20to%20mainstream%20frameworks.%20The%20Dalit-Bahujan%20attempts%20at%20memorialisation%20are%20often%20ridiculed%20and%20treated%20as%20manifestations%20of%20emotional%20and%20irrational%20deifications.%20It%20is%20no%20coincidence%20that%20until%201990%2C%20there%20was%20no%20portrait%20of%20Ambedkar%20in%20the%20central%20hall%20of%20the%20parliament.%20Simultaneously%2C%20it%20was%20only%20after%20continuous%20campaigns%20conducted%20across%20Maharashtra%20from%20the%201980s%20onwards%20that%20the%20historical%20sites%20associated%20with%20Jyotirao%20and%20Savitribai%20Phule%20were%20converted%20into%20protected%20monuments.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20unlike%20Bhide%20Wada%2C%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20monuments%20in%20Maharashtra%20seldom%20depend%20on%20state%20patronage%20and%20support.%20Monuments%20like%20Chaitya%20Bhoomi%20and%20Deekshabhoomi%20have%20become%20significant%20sites%20of%20assertion%20that%20help%20the%20erstwhile%20untouchables%20navigate%20beyond%20stigma%20and%20humiliation.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20memorialisation%20of%20the%20monuments%20associated%20with%20the%20anti-caste%20movement%20is%20essential%20for%20Dalit%20and%20OBC%20movements%20to%20steer%20through%20dominant%20interpretations%20of%20culture.%20Creating%20such%20sites%20of%20memorialisation%20also%20helps%20democratise%20the%20overall%20political%20and%20cultural%20ambience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20monuments%20like%20Bhide%20Wada%20are%20not%20just%20physical%20structures.%20They%20can%20pose%20a%20real%20challenge%20to%20the%20dominant%20forms%20of%20power.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20if%20Bhide%20Wada%20becomes%20a%20temple%20of%20deification%20of%20Savitribai%20and%20Jyotirao%2C%20it%20will%20generate%20counterproductive%20results.%20In%20the%20new%20context%2C%20whatever%20affirmative%20feelings%20it%20evokes%2C%20there%20is%20a%20greater%20risk%20of%20such%20sites%20becoming%20banal%20and%20apolitical%20locations%20of%20identity%20creation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fprabodhan-pol%5C%22%3EPrabodhan%20Pol%3C%2Fa%3E%20teaches%20at%20Manipal%20Centre%20for%20Humanities%20MAHE%2C%20Manipal%20(Karnataka).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703145922000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21132757%2FFH_m4ZgVIAMpUgL.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbhide-wada-long-lasting-legacy-phules-school%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bystanders%20who%20were%20oblivious%20to%20its%20historical%20significance%20may%20have%20thought%20of%20Bhide%20Wada%20as%20just%20another%20dilapidated%20building%2C%20but%20it%20set%20the%20tone%20for%20new%20voices%20of%20cultural%20expression.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbhide-wada-long-lasting-legacy-phules-school%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Panel%20Chair%20'Concerned'%20Over%20Suspension%20of%20Indian%20Opposition%20MPs%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F21133055%2FScreenshot-2023-12-21-at-1.29.01.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Expressing%20concern%20over%20the%20mass%20suspension%20of%20opposition%20lawmakers%20in%20India%2C%20US%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Committee%20Chair%20Ben%20Cardin%20has%20highlighted%20the%20need%20for%20democracies%20to%20devise%20strategies%20for%20enabling%20%E2%80%9Copen%20debate%20and%20maintaining%20security%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20ongoing%20parliamentary%20session%2C%20143%20members%20of%20parliament%20were%20suspended%20for%20demanding%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20breach